INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3585, '1998考研英语', 'Choose the best one and mark your answer on ANSWER SHEET 1 by blackening the corresponding letter in the brackets with a pencil.', '选择最好的答案，并在答题纸1上用铅笔将括号中相应的字母涂黑。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3586, '1998考研英语', 'They1that in the long run industrialization greatly raised the standard of living for the 2 man.', '从长远来看，工业化极大地提高了两个人的生活水平。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3587, '1998考研英语', 'This view, 7 , is generally thought to be wrong.', '这种观点，7，一般认为是错误的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3588, '1998考研英语', 'Read the passages carefully and choose the best answer to each of the questions.', '仔细阅读短文，并选择每个问题的最佳答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3589, '1998考研英语', 'Then mark your answer on the ANSWER SHEET 1 by blackening the corresponding letter in the brackets.', '然后在答题纸1上标记你的答案，把括号中相应的字母涂黑。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3590, '1998考研英语', 'But to be fascinated is also, sometimes, to be blind.', '但着迷有时也是盲目的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3591, '1998考研英语', 'Several giant dam projects threaten to do more harm than good.', '几个大型水坝工程可能弊大于利。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3592, '1998考研英语', 'The lesson from dams is that big is not always beautiful.', '从水坝中得到的教训是，大坝并不总是美丽的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3593, '1998考研英语', 'But big dams tend not to work as intended.', '但大型水坝往往无法按预期工作。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3594, '1998考研英语', 'And yet, the myth of controlling the waters persists.', '然而，控制水的神话依然存在。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3595, '1998考研英语', 'This week, in the heart of civilized Europe, Slovaks and Hungarians stopped just short of sending in the troops in their contention over a dam on the Danube.', '本周，在文明欧洲的心脏地带，斯洛伐克人和匈牙利人停止了派遣军队参加多瑙河的大坝争夺战。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3596, '1998考研英语', 'The huge complex will probably have all the usual problems of big dams.', '庞大的建筑群可能会遇到大坝的所有常见问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3597, '1998考研英语', 'But Slovakia is bidding for independence from the Czechs, and now needs a dam to prove itself.', '但是斯洛伐克正在争取脱离捷克的独立，现在需要一个大坝来证明自己。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3598, '1998考研英语', 'And the bank has done this even though its advisors say the dam will cause hardship for the powerless and environmental destruction.', '世行已经做到了这一点，尽管它的顾问们说，大坝将给无能为力和环境破坏造成困难。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3599, '1998考研英语', 'The benefits are for the powerful, but they are far from guaranteed.', '好处是有权势的，但远不能保证。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3600, '1998考研英语', 'Proper, scientific study of the impacts of dams and of the cost and benefits of controlling water can help to resolve these conflicts.', '适当、科学地研究大坝的影响以及控制水的成本和效益可以帮助解决这些冲突。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3601, '1998考研英语', 'Hydroelectric power and flood control and irrigation are possible without building monster dams.', '水力发电和洪水控制和灌溉是不可能建造巨型水坝的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3602, '1998考研英语', 'But when you are dealing with myths, it is hard to be either proper, or scientific.', '但是，当你处理神话时，很难是正确的或科学的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3603, '1998考研英语', 'It is time that the world learned the lessons of Aswan.', '现在是世界吸取阿斯旺教训的时候了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3604, '1998考研英语', 'What is the myth concerning giant dams.', '关于巨型水坝的神话是什么？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3605, '1998考研英语', 'But what about pain without gain.', '但是没有收获的痛苦呢？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3606, '1998考研英语', 'Everywhere you go in America, you hear tales of corporate revival.', '无论你去美国，你都会听到企业复兴的故事。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3607, '1998考研英语', 'What is harder to establish is whether the productivity revolution that businessmen assume they are presiding over is for real.', '更难确定的是，商人们认为他们正在主持的生产力革命是否是真的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3608, '1998考研英语', 'The official statistics are mildly discouraging.', '官方统计数据令人沮丧。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3609, '1998考研英语', 'They show that, if you lump manufacturing and services together, productivity has grown on average by 1.', '他们表明，如果你把制造业和服务业结合在一起，生产力平均增长了1。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3610, '1998考研英语', 'That is somewhat faster than the average during the previous decade.', '这比前十年的平均速度要快一些。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3611, '1998考研英语', 'The trouble is that part of the recent acceleration is due to the usual rebound that occurs at this point in a business cycle, and so is not conclusive evidence of a revival in the underlying trend.', '问题在于，近期经济加速的部分原因是由于商业周期中此时出现的通常反弹，因此不是潜在趋势复苏的确凿证据。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3612, '1998考研英语', 'There is, as Robert Rubin, the treasury secretary, says, a \"disjunction\" between the mass of business anecdote that points to a leap in productivity and the picture reflected by the statistics.', '正如美国财政部长罗伯特·鲁宾（Robert Rubin）所说，大量商业轶事表明生产力的飞跃，与统计数字所反映的情况之间存在“脱节”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3613, '1998考研英语', 'Some of this can be easily explained.', '其中有些可以很容易地解释。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3614, '1998考研英语', 'Moreover, most of the changes that companies make are intended to keep them profitable, and this need not always mean increasing productivity: switching to new markets or improving quality can matter just as much.', '此外，公司所做的大多数改变都是为了保持盈利，而这并不一定意味着提高生产率：转向新市场或提高质量同样重要。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3615, '1998考研英语', 'Two other explanations are more speculative.', '另外两种解释更具推测性。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3616, '1998考研英语', 'First, some of the business restructuring of recent years may have been ineptly done.', '首先，最近几年的一些业务重组可能已经做得不好。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3617, '1998考研英语', 'Second, even if it was well done, it may have spread much less widely than people suppose.', '第二，即使它做得很好，它传播的可能性也比人们想象的要小得多。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3618, '1998考研英语', 'In many cases, he believes, the loss of revenue has been greater than the reductions in cost.', '他认为，在许多情况下，收入的损失大于成本的降低。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3619, '1998考研英语', 'The author raises the question \"what about pain without gain.', '作者提出了一个问题：“无利可图的痛苦”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3620, '1998考研英语', 'Which of the following statements is NOT mentioned in the passage.', '下列哪个陈述在文章中没有提及？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3621, '1998考研英语', 'Science has long had an uneasy relationship with other aspects of culture.', '科学长期以来与文化的其他方面有着不安的关系。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3622, '1998考研英语', 'The schism between science and the humanities has, if anything, deepened in this century.', '科学和人文科学之间的分裂在这个世纪已经加深了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3623, '1998考研英语', 'Defenders of science have also voiced their concerns at meetings such as \"The Flight from Science and Reason,\" held in New York City in 1995, and \"Science in the Age of (Mis) information,\" which assembled last June near Buffalo.', '科学捍卫者还在1995年在纽约市举行的“科学与理性之旅”以及去年6月在布法罗附近召开的“信息时代的科学”等会议上表达了他们的关切。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3624, '1998考研英语', 'Sagan is more concerned with those who believe in ghosts, creationism and other phenomena that contradict the scientific worldview.', '萨根更关心那些相信鬼魂、神创论和其他与科学世界观相悖的现象。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3625, '1998考研英语', 'The true enemies of science, argues Paul Ehrlich of Stanford University, a pioneer of environmental studies, are those who question the evidence supporting global warming, the depletion of the ozone layer and other consequences of industrial growth.', '环境研究的先驱、斯坦福大学的保罗·埃利希认为，科学的真正敌人是那些质疑支持全球变暖、臭氧层损耗和工业增长的其他后果的证据的人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3626, '1998考研英语', '\"They have in common only one thing that they tend to annoy or threaten those who regard themselves as more enlightened.', '“他们只有一个共同点，那就是他们往往惹恼或威胁那些认为自己更开明的人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3627, '1998考研英语', 'Which of the following is true according to the passage.', '根据文章，下列哪一项是正确的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3628, '1998考研英语', 'Even so, that gain adds up to only 11.', '即便如此，这一涨幅仅为11。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3629, '1998考研英语', '4 percent, lowest in American annual records except for the Depression years.', '4%，除萧条年代外，美国年报最低。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3630, '1998考研英语', 'Americans have been migrating south and west in larger numbers since World War II, and the pattern still prevails.', '自第二次世界大战以来，美国人大量移民南部和西部，这种模式仍然盛行。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3631, '1998考研英语', 'Not all that shift can be attributed to the movement out of the snow belt, census officials say.', '普查官员说，并不是所有的变化都可以归因于雪地带的运动。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3632, '1998考研英语', 'Moreover, demographers see the continuing shift south and west as joined by a related but newer phenomenon: More and more, Americans apparently are looking not just for places with more jobs but with fewer people, too.', '此外，人口统计学家认为，南部和西部的持续变化伴随着一个相关但较新的现象：越来越多的美国人显然不仅在寻找有更多工作的地方，而且也在寻找人口较少的地方。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3633, '1998考研英语', '1 percent respectively.', '1%。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3634, '1998考研英语', 'The flight from overcrowdedness affects the migration from snow belt to more bearable climates.', '来自过度拥挤的飞行影响了从雪带到更易忍受的气候的迁移。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3635, '1998考研英语', 'There, California added 3.', '在那里，加利福尼亚增加了3。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3636, '1998考研英语', 'In that decade, however, large numbers also migrated from California, mostly to other parts of the West.', '然而，在这十年里，大量的人口也从加利福尼亚迁移到了西方的其他地区。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3637, '1998考研英语', 'Most of the hot spots move only slowly, and in some cases the movement of the plates past them has left trails of dead volcanoes.', '大多数热点只是缓慢地移动，在某些情况下板块移动经过它们留下了死火山的痕迹。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3638, '1998考研英语', 'The hot spots and their volcanic trails are milestones that mark the passage of the plates.', '热点和火山轨迹是标志板块通过的里程碑。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3639, '1998考研英语', 'That the plates are moving is now beyond dispute.', '板块正在移动，现在已经无可争议。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3640, '1998考研英语', 'Africa and South America, for example, are moving away from each other as new material is injected into the sea floor between them.', '例如，非洲和南美洲正在彼此远离，因为新材料被注入它们之间的海底。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3641, '1998考研英语', 'The complementary coastlines and certain geological features that seem to span the ocean are reminders of where the two continents were once joined.', '的海岸线和某些地质特征表明跨越海洋这两个大陆曾经。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3642, '1998考研英语', 'It is not possible to determine whether both continents are moving in opposite directions or whether one continent is stationary and the other is drifting away from it.', '不可能确定两个大陆是否在相反的方向上移动，或者一个大陆是否静止，而另一个大陆是否正在远离它。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3643, '1998考研英语', 'Hot spots, anchored in the deeper layers of the earth, provide the measuring instruments needed to resolve the question.', '热点，锚定在更深层次的地球，提供测量仪器需要解决这个问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3644, '1998考研英语', 'The significance of hot spots is not confined to their role as a frame of reference.', '热点的意义并不局限于它们作为参照系的作用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3645, '1998考研英语', 'It now appears that they also have an important influence on the geophysical processes that propel the plates across the globe.', '现在看来，它们也对推动地球板块运动的地球物理过程产生重要影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3646, '1998考研英语', 'When a continental plate come to rest over a hot spot, the material rising from deeper layers creates a broad dome.', '当大陆板块停留在一个热点上时，从深层升起的物质会形成一个宽阔的圆顶。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3647, '1998考研英语', 'Thus just as earlier theories have explained the mobility of the continents, so hot spots may explain their mutability (inconstancy).', '因此，正如早期的理论解释了大陆的移动性，所以热点可以解释大陆的易变性。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3648, '1998考研英语', 'Your translation must be written clearly on the ANSWER SHEET 2.', '你的翻译必须写在答题纸2上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3649, '1998考研英语', '31) But even more important, it was the farthest that scientists had been able to look into the past, for what they were seeing were the patterns and structures that existed 15 billion years ago.', '31)但更重要的是，这是科学家们所能看到的最遥远的过去，因为他们看到的是150亿年前存在的模式和结构。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3650, '1998考研英语', 'That was just about the moment that the universe was born.', '就在宇宙诞生的那一刻。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3651, '1998考研英语', 'According to the theory, the universe burst into being as a submicroscopic, unimaginably dense knot of pure energy that flew outward in all directions, emitting radiation as it went, condensing into particles and then into atoms of gas.', '根据这个理论，宇宙爆发成一个亚微观的、不可想象的密集在一起的纯能量结，它向四面八方飞去，随着它的移动放射出辐射，凝结成粒子，然后变成气体原子。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3652, '1998考研英语', 'Over billions of years, the gas was compressed by gravity into galaxies, stars, plants and eventually, even humans.', '几十亿年来，气体被重力压缩成星系，恒星，植物，甚至人类。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3653, '1998考研英语', 'Cobe is designed to see just the biggest structures, but astronomers would like to see much smaller hot spots as well, the seeds of local objects like clusters and superclusters of galaxies.', 'Cobe被设计成只看到最大的结构，但是天文学家也想看到更小的热点，像星系团和超级星系团这样的局部天体的种子。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3654, '1998考研英语', '34) If the small hot spots look as expected, that will be a triumph for yet another scientific idea, a refinement of the Big Bang called the inflationary universe theory.', '34)如果这些小热点看起来像预期的那样，那将是又一个科学思想的胜利，一个大爆炸的精细化，称为宇宙膨胀理论。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3655, '1998考研英语', 'Inflation says that very early on, the universe expanded in size by more than a trillion trillion trillion trillion fold in much less than a second, propelled by a sort of antigravity.', '通货膨胀说，很早以前，由于某种反重力的推动，宇宙在不到一秒的时间里膨胀了超过一万亿万亿万亿倍。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3656, '1998考研英语', '35) Odd though it sounds, cosmic inflation is a scientifically plausible consequence of some respected ideas in elementary particle physics, and many astrophysicists have been convinced for the better part of a decade that it is true.', '35)虽然听起来很奇怪，宇宙膨胀是基本粒子物理中一些受人尊敬的观念的科学上合理的结果，许多天体物理学家在近十年的大部分时间里都相信这是真的。');
