INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3713, '1999考研英语', 'Then mark your answer on ANSWER SHEET 1 by blackening the corresponding letter in the brackets with a pencil.', '然后用铅笔将括号中的相应字母黑化，在答题纸1上标上答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3714, '1999考研英语', 'Step outside and you could break a leg slipping on your doormat.', '走到外面，你就会摔断你的门垫上的一条腿。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3715, '1999考研英语', 'Light up the stove and you could burn down the house.', '点燃炉子，你就可以把房子烧掉。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3716, '1999考研英语', 'Luckily, if the doormat or stove failed to warn of coming disaster, a successful lawsuit might compensate you for your troubles.', '幸运的是，如果门垫或炉子没有警告即将到来的灾难，成功的诉讼可能会补偿你的麻烦。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3717, '1999考研英语', 'Now the tide appears to be turning.', '现在潮流似乎正在转向。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3718, '1999考研英语', 'In May, Julie Nimmons, president of Schutt Sports in Illinois, successfully fought a lawsuit involving a football player who was paralyzed in a game while wearing a Schutt helmet.', '今年五月，伊利诺伊州舒特体育的总裁朱莉·尼蒙斯成功地打赢了一场官司，官司涉及一名足球运动员，他戴着舒特头盔在比赛中瘫痪。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3719, '1999考研英语', 'At the same time, the American Law Institute—a group of judges, lawyers, and academics whose recommendations carry substantial weight—issued new guidelines for tort law stating that companies need not warn customers of obvious dangers or bombard them with', '与此同时，由法官、律师和学者组成的团体——美国法律研究所发布了新的侵权行为法指导方针，该指导方针具有重大意义，规定公司不必警告顾客明显的危险或用炸弹轰炸顾客。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3720, '1999考研英语', '\"Important information can get buried in a sea of trivialities, \" says a law professor at Cornell Law School who helped draft the new guidelines.', '康奈尔法学院（Cornell Law School）的一位协助起草新指南的法律教授说：“重要的信息可能会被埋没在琐碎的海洋中。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3721, '1999考研英语', 'If the moderate end of the legal community has its way, the information on products might actually be provided for the benefit of customers and not as protection against legal liability.', '如果法律界的温和派有自己的方式，那么提供有关产品的信息可能实际上是为了顾客的利益，而不是为了防止法律责任。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3722, '1999考研英语', 'Manufacturers as mentioned in the passage tend to.', '正如文章中提到的制造商倾向于这样做。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3723, '1999考研英语', 'The case of Schutt helmet demonstrated that.', 'Suutt头盔的例子证明了这一点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3724, '1999考研英语', 'More recently, as the Web proved to be more than a fashion, companies have started to buy and sell products and services with one another.', '最近，随着网络被证明不仅仅是一种时尚，公司已经开始相互购买和销售产品和服务。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3725, '1999考研英语', 'to business sales make sense because business people Nonetheless, many companies still hesitate to use the Web because of doubts about its reliability.', '对企业的销售有意义因为生意人尽管如此，很多公司还是毫不犹豫地使用网络由于怀疑网络的可靠性。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3726, '1999考研英语', 'Another major shift in the model for Internet commerce concerns the technology available for marketing.', '互联网商务模式的另一个重大转变涉及到可用于市场营销的技术。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3727, '1999考研英语', 'Until recently, Internet marketing activities have focused on strategies to \"pull\" customers into sites.', '直到最近，网络营销活动都集中在将顾客拉入网站的策略上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3728, '1999考研英语', 'In the past year, however, software companies have developed tools that allow companies to \"push\" information directly out to consumers, transmitting marketing messages directly to targeted customers.', '然而，在过去的一年中，软件公司已经开发了一些工具，允许公司“推出”信息直接给消费者，将营销信息直接传递给目标客户。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3729, '1999考研英语', 'Companies such as Virtual Vineyards are already starting to use similar technologies to push messages to customers about special sales, product offerings, or other events.', '像VirtualVine.s这样的公司已经开始使用类似的技术来向客户传递关于特殊销售、产品供应或其他活动的信息。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3730, '1999考研英语', 'But push technology has earned the contempt of many Web users.', '但是推送技术已经赢得了许多网络用户的轻蔑。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3731, '1999考研英语', 'Online culture thinks highly of the notion that the information flowing onto the screen comes there by specific request.', '在线文化高度重视信息流到屏幕上的具体要求。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3732, '1999考研英语', 'Once commercial promotion begins to fill the screen uninvited, the distinction between the Web and television fades.', '一旦商业推广开始不请自来，网络和电视之间的区别就会消失。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3733, '1999考研英语', 'But it is hardly inevitable that companies on the Web will need to resort to push strategies to make money.', '但是，网络上的公司很难采取推动策略来赚钱。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3734, '1999考研英语', 'The examples of Virtual Vineyards, Amazon.', '虚拟葡萄园的例子，Amazon。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3735, '1999考研英语', 'com, and other pioneers show that a Web site selling the right kind of products with the right mix of interactivity, hospitality, and security will attract online customers.', 'com和其他先驱者表明，一个销售具有交互性、好客性和安全性的合适组合的正确类型的产品的网站将吸引在线客户。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3736, '1999考研英语', 'And the cost of computing power continues to free fall, which is a good sign for any enterprise setting up shop in silicon.', '而且计算能力的成本继续自由下降，这是任何企业在硅上建立商店的好兆头。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3737, '1999考研英语', 'We learn from the beginning of the passage that Web business.', '我们从文章的开头就学到了网络业务。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3738, '1999考研英语', 'Speaking of the online technology available for marketing, the author implies that.', '谈到在线技术可用于市场营销，作者暗示。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3739, '1999考研英语', 'In the view of Net purists,.', '从净化器的角度来看。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3740, '1999考研英语', 'We learn from the last paragraph that.', '我们从最后一段中学到。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3741, '1999考研英语', 'An education that aims at getting a student a certain kind of job is a technical education, justified for reasons radically different from why education is universally required by law.', '旨在使学生获得某种工作的教育是技术教育，其理由与法律普遍要求教育的理由完全不同。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3742, '1999考研英语', 'Rather, we have a certain conception of the American citizen, a character who is incomplete if he cannot competently assess how his livelihood and happiness are affected by things outside of himself.', '相反，我们对美国公民有某种概念，如果他不能恰当地评估自己的生活和幸福是如何受到自身之外的事物影响的，那么这个人物就是不完整的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3743, '1999考研英语', 'With optimism characteristic of all industrialized countries, we came to accept that everyone is fit to be educated.', '在所有工业化国家的乐观主义特征下，我们开始接受每个人都适合接受教育。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3744, '1999考研英语', 'Computer education advocates forsake this optimistic notion for a pessimism that betrays their otherwise cheery outlook.', '计算机教育倡导者摒弃了这种乐观主义观点，认为悲观主义会背弃他们乐观的观点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3745, '1999考研英语', 'Banking on the confusion between educational and vocational reasons for bringing computers into schools, computered advocates often emphasize the job prospects of graduates over their educational achievement.', '考虑到将计算机引入学校的教育原因和职业原因之间的混淆，计算机倡导者经常强调毕业生的工作前景而不是他们的教育成就。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3746, '1999考研英语', 'There are some good arguments for a technical education given the right kind of student.', '对于合适的学生来说，技术教育有一些很好的理由。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3747, '1999考研英语', 'Many European schools introduce the concept of professional training early on in order to make sure children are properly equipped for the professions they want to join.', '许多欧洲学校很早就引进了专业培训的概念，以确保孩子们能够适当地适应他们想加入的职业。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3748, '1999考研英语', 'It is, however, presumptuous to insist that there will only be so many jobs for so many scientists, so many businessmen, so many accountants.', '然而，坚持认为只有这么多的科学家，这么多的商人，这么多的会计师才有这么多的工作是冒昧的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3749, '1999考研英语', 'Besides, this is unlikely to produce the needed number of every kind of professional in a country as large as ours and where the economy is spread over so many states and involves so many international corporations.', '此外，在一个像我们这么大的国家，而且经济分布在如此多的国家，涉及如此多的国际公司，这是不太可能产生所需要的各种专业人员的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3750, '1999考研英语', 'But, for a small group of students, professional training might be the way to go since well developed skills, all other factors being equal, can be the difference between having a job and not.', '但是，对于一小部分学生来说，专业培训可能是一种方式，因为发达的技能，所有其他因素都一样，可能是有工作与没有工作的区别。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3751, '1999考研英语', 'Of course, the basics of using any computer these days are very simple.', '当然，现在使用任何计算机的基本原理都很简单。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3752, '1999考研英语', 'It does not take a lifelong acquaintance to pick up various software programs.', '它不需要一生的熟人来收集各种软件程序。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3753, '1999考研英语', 'If one wanted to become a computer engineer, that is, of course, an entirely different story.', '如果想成为一名计算机工程师，那当然是一个完全不同的故事。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3754, '1999考研英语', 'Basic computer skills take—at the very longest—a couple of months to learn.', '基本的计算机技能需要花很长时间才能学习。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3755, '1999考研英语', 'In any case, basic computer skills are only complementary to the host of real skills that are necessary to becoming any kind of professional.', '在任何情况下，基本的计算机技能只是与成为任何专业人员所必需的真正技能的补充。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3756, '1999考研英语', 'It should be observed, of course, that no school, vocational or not, is helped by a confusion over its purpose.', '当然，应该观察到，没有学校，无论职业与否，都有助于对其目的的混淆。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3757, '1999考研英语', 'The author thinks the present rush to put computers in the classroom is.', '作者认为，现在把计算机放在教室里是一件急事。');
