INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3759, '1999考研英语', 'According to the author, basic computer skills should be.', '作者认为，基本的计算机技能应该是。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3760, '1999考研英语', 'That group—the National Bioethics Advisory Commission (NBAC)—has been working feverishly to put its wisdom on paper, and at a meeting on 17 May, members agreed on a near final draft of their recommendations.', '这个组织——国家生物伦理学咨询委员会（NBAC）——一直在狂热地工作，以将其智慧写在纸上，在5月17日的会议上，成员们商定了一份接近最后草案的建议。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3761, '1999考研英语', 'But NBAC members are planning to word the recommendation narrowly to avoid new restrictions on research that involves the cloning of human DNA or cells—routine in molecular biology.', '但是，NBAC成员们正计划狭义地提出这项建议，以避免对涉及克隆人类DNA或细胞的研究的新限制——分子生物学中的常规。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3762, '1999考研英语', 'The panel has not yet reached agreement on a crucial question, however, whether to recommend legislation that would make it a crime for private funding to be used for human cloning.', '然而，该小组尚未就一个关键问题达成协议，即是否建议立法将私人资金用于克隆人定为犯罪。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3763, '1999考研英语', 'In a draft preface to the recommendations, discussed at the 17 May meeting, Shapiro suggested that the panel had found a broad consensus that it would be \"morally unacceptable to attempt to create a human child by adult nuclear cloning.', '在5月17日会议上讨论的这些建议的序言草案中，夏皮罗建议该小组已经达成广泛共识，即“试图通过成人核克隆来创造人类儿童在道义上是不可接受的”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3764, '1999考研英语', '\" Shapiro explained during the meeting that the moral doubt stems mainly from fears about the risk to the health of the child.', '夏皮罗在会上解释道，道德上的怀疑主要源于对孩子健康风险的担忧。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3765, '1999考研英语', 'The panel then informally accepted several general conclusions, although some details have not been settled.', '该小组随后非正式地接受了一些一般性结论，尽管一些细节尚未得到解决。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3766, '1999考研英语', 'NBAC plans to call for a continued ban on federal government funding for any attempt to clone body cell nuclei to create a child.', 'NBAC计划呼吁继续禁止联邦政府资助任何克隆体细胞核的尝试，以创造一个孩子。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3767, '1999考研英语', 'NBAC members also indicated that they would appeal to privately funded researchers and clinics not to try to clone humans by body cell nuclear transfer.', 'NBAC成员还表示，他们将呼吁私人资助的研究人员和诊所不要试图通过体细胞核移植来克隆人类。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3768, '1999考研英语', 'But they were divided on whether to go further by calling for a federal law that would impose a complete ban on human cloning.', '但他们对是否进一步呼吁联邦法律实施全面禁止人类克隆而分歧。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3769, '1999考研英语', 'Shapiro and most members favored an appeal for such legislation, but in a phone interview, he said this issue was still \"up in the air\".', '夏皮罗和大多数成员赞成呼吁立法，但在电话采访中，他说，这个问题仍然“悬而未决”。');
