INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3790, '1999考研英语', '\" The scientist has been shocked at having even been asked to speculate.', '“科学家甚至被要求推测，感到震惊。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3791, '1999考研英语', 'What this amounts to, of course, is that the scientist has become the victim of his own writings.', '当然，这也意味着科学家已经成为他自己作品的牺牲品。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3792, '1999考研英语', 'He has put forward unquestioned claims so consistently that he not only believes them himself, but has convinced industrial and business management that they are true.', '他始终如一地提出毫无疑问的主张，以至于他不仅相信自己，而且使工业和企业管理层相信他们是真的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3793, '1999考研英语', 'If experiments are planned and carried out according to plan as faithfully as the reports in the science journals indicate, then it is perfectly logical for management to expect research to produce results measurable in dollars and cents.', '如果实验是按照科学期刊上的报告指出的那样忠实地按照计划计划计划和实施的，那么管理层期望研究产生可以用美元和美分衡量的结果是完全合乎逻辑的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3794, '1999考研英语', 'It is entirely reasonable for auditors to believe that scientists who know exactly where they are going and how they will get there should not be distracted by the necessity of keeping one eye on the cash register while the other eye is on the microscope.', '审计人员完全有理由相信，那些知道自己要去哪里以及如何到达那里的科学家不应该因为必须一只眼睛盯着收银机，而另一只眼睛盯着显微镜而分心。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3795, '1999考研英语', 'Nor, if regularity and conformity to a standard pattern are as desirable to the scientist as the writing of his papers would appear to reflect, is management to be blamed for discriminating against the \"odd balls\" among researchers in favor of more conven', '如果科学家像他论文的写作所反映的那样希望有规律和符合标准模式，那么管理层也不应该因为歧视研究人员中的“奇数球”而受到指责，而倾向于更平易近人。');
