INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3949, '2001考研英语', 'In a letter to Gerald Kaufman, chairman of the House of Commons media select committee, Lord Irvine said he 7 with a committee report this year which said that self regulation did not 8 sufficient control.', '欧文勋爵在给下议院媒体特别委员会主席杰拉尔德·考夫曼的一封信中说，他今年带着一份委员会报告，报告说自我监管没有得到充分的控制。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3950, '2001考研英语', 'The Lord Chancellor said introduction of the Human Rights Bill, which 13 the European Convention on Human Rights legally 14 in Britain, laid down that everybody was 15 to privacy and that public figures could go to court to protect themselves and their fa', '英国总理说，人权法案的出台，其中13的欧洲人权公约在法律上是14的，规定每个人都有15的隐私权，公众人物可以去法院保护他们自己和他们的FA。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3951, '2001考研英语', '\"Press freedoms will be in safe hands 16 our British judges,\" he said.', '他说：“我们的英国法官有16的新闻自由。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3952, '2001考研英语', 'Up to 19 witnesses were 18 to have received payments for telling their stories to newspapers.', '多达19名证人收到了18份给报纸讲故事的费用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3953, '2001考研英语', 'Read the passages carefully and choose the best answer to each of the questions.', '仔细阅读段落，选择每个问题的最佳答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3954, '2001考研英语', 'Then mark your answer on ANSWER SHEET 1 by blackening the corresponding letter in the brackets with a pencil.', '然后用铅笔将括号中的相应字母黑化，在答题纸1上标上答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3955, '2001考研英语', 'By splitting up the subject matter into smaller units,one man could continue to handle the information and use it as the basis for further research.', '通过将主题分成较小的单元，一个人可以继续处理这些信息，并将其作为进一步研究的基础。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3956, '2001考研英语', 'But specialisation was only one of a series of related developments in science affecting the process of communication.', '但专业化只是影响科学传播过程的一系列相关发展中的一个。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3957, '2001考研英语', 'Another was the growing professionalisation of scientific activity.', '另一个原因是科学活动的日益专业化。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3958, '2001考研英语', 'Nevertheless, the word \"amateur\" does carry a connotation that the person concerned is not fully integrated into the scientific community and, in particular, may not fully share its values.', '然而，“业余”一词的确具有这样的含义，即相关人员没有完全融入科学界，特别是可能没有完全分享其价值。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3959, '2001考研英语', 'The growth of specialisation in the nineteenth century, with its consequent requirement of a longer, more complex training, implied greater problems for amateur participation in science.', '19世纪专业化的发展，随之而来的需要更长、更复杂的培训，暗示了业余参与科学的更大问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3960, '2001考研英语', 'The trend was naturally most obvious in those areas of science based especially on a mathematical or laboratory training, and can be illustrated in terms of the development of geology in the United Kingdom.', '这种趋势在那些以数学或实验室训练为基础的科学领域自然是最明显的，并且可以从英国地质学发展的角度加以说明。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3961, '2001考研英语', 'A comparison of British geological publications over the last century and a half reveals not simply an increasing emphasis on the primacy of research, but also a changing definition of what constitutes an acceptable research paper.', '比较英国地质出版物在过去一个半世纪中，不仅揭示了越来越重视研究的首要地位，而且也改变了什么构成一个可接受的研究论文的定义。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3962, '2001考研英语', 'Amateurs, on the other hand, have continued to pursue local studies in the old way.', '另一方面，业余爱好者则以旧的方式继续从事当地的研究。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3963, '2001考研英语', 'As a logical consequence of this development, separate journals have now appeared aimed mainly towards either professional or amateur readership.', '由于这种发展的逻辑结果，现在出现了以专业或业余读者为主要读者群的独立期刊。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3964, '2001考研英语', 'A rather similar process of differentiation has led to professional geologists coming together nationally within one or two specific societies, whereas the amateurs have tended either to remain in local societies or to come together nationally in a differ', '一个相当类似的分化过程导致专业地质学家在一个或两个特定的协会内聚集在全国，而业余地质学家则倾向于留在当地协会，或者以不同的方式聚集在全国。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3965, '2001考研英语', 'Although the process of professionalisation and specialisation was already well under way in British geology during the nineteenth century, its full consequences were thus delayed until the twentieth century.', '虽然19世纪英国地质学专业化和专业化的进程已经开始，但其全部后果被推迟到二十世纪。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3966, '2001考研英语', 'In science generally, however, the nineteenth century must be reckoned as the crucial period for this change in the structure of science.', '然而，在科学领域，19世纪必须被看作是科学结构发生这种变化的关键时期。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3967, '2001考研英语', 'And that divide does exist today.', '这种分歧确实存在。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3968, '2001考研英语', 'My wife and I lectured about this looming danger twenty years ago.', '二十年前，我和我的妻子谈到了这一迫在眉睫的危险。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3969, '2001考研英语', 'What was less visible then, however, were the new, positive forces that work against the digital divide.', '然而，当时不那么明显的是，对抗数字鸿沟的新的积极力量。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3970, '2001考研英语', 'There are reasons to be optimistic.', '有理由乐观。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3971, '2001考研英语', 'There are technological reasons to hope the digital divide will narrow.', '有技术原因希望数字鸿沟会缩小。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3972, '2001考研英语', 'And behind, want to spread Internet access.', '而背后，则想传播互联网接入。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3973, '2001考研英语', 'Within the next decade or two, one to two billion people on the planet will he netted together.', '在未来的十年或二十年内，地球上有一到二十亿人会聚集在一起。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3974, '2001考研英语', 'As a result, I now believe the digital divide will narrow rather than widen in the years ahead.', '因此，我现在相信数字鸿沟在未来几年会缩小而不是变宽。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3975, '2001考研英语', 'the Internet is not the only tool we have.', '互联网并不是我们拥有的唯一工具。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3976, '2001考研英语', 'But it has enormous potential.', '但它具有巨大的潜力。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3977, '2001考研英语', 'Immigrant Americans built them.', '移民美国人建造了他们。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3978, '2001考研英语', 'Guess who owns them now.', '猜猜现在谁拥有它们。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3979, '2001考研英语', 'I believe the same thing would be true in places like Brazil or anywhere else for that matter.', '我相信同样的事情在巴西和其他任何地方都是如此。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3980, '2001考研英语', 'That doesn\'t mean lying down and becoming fooled, or letting foreign corporations run uncontrolled.', '这并不意味着撒谎和被愚弄，或者让外国公司失控。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3981, '2001考研英语', 'But it does mean recognizing how important they can be in building the energy and telecom infrastructures needed to take full advantage of the Internet.', '但这确实意味着认识到它们在建设充分利用互联网所需的能源和电信基础设施方面有多么重要。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3982, '2001考研英语', 'The American Society of Newspaper Editors is trying to answer this painful question.', '美国报纸编辑协会正试图回答这个痛苦的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3983, '2001考研英语', 'But the sources of distrust go way deeper.', '但不信任的来源更为深远。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3984, '2001考研英语', 'There exists a social and cultural disconnect between journalists and their readers which helps explain why the \"standard templates\"of the newsroom seem alien many readers.', '新闻记者和读者之间存在着社会和文化的脱节，这有助于解释为什么新闻编辑室的“标准模板”似乎与许多读者格格不入。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3985, '2001考研英语', 'In a recent survey, questionnaires were sent to reporters in five middle size cities around the country, plus one large metropolitan area.', '在最近的一次调查中，向全国五个中等城市和一个大城市的记者发送了调查问卷。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3986, '2001考研英语', 'Then residents in these communities were phoned at random and asked the same questions.', '然后这些社区的居民被随机打电话问同样的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3987, '2001考研英语', 'Reporters tend to be part of a broadly defined social and cultural elite, so their work tends to reflect the conventional values of this elite.', '记者往往是一个广泛定义的社会和文化精英的一部分，所以他们的工作往往反映这个精英的传统价值观。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3988, '2001考研英语', 'This is an explosive situation for any industry, particularly a declining one.', '这对于任何行业来说都是一个爆炸性的形势，尤其是衰退的行业。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3989, '2001考研英语', 'Here is a troubled business that keeps hiring employees whose attitudes vastly annoy the customers.', '这是一个麻烦不断的业务，不断雇佣员工，他们的态度极大地困扰着客户。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3990, '2001考研英语', 'Then it sponsors lots of symposiums and a credibility project dedicated to wondering why customers are annoyed and fleeing in large numbers.', '然后，它赞助了很多研讨会和一个信誉项目，专门研究为什么客户会感到烦恼，并且大量逃离。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3991, '2001考研英语', 'But it never seems to get around to noticing the cultural and class biases that so many former buyers are complaining about.', '但似乎从来没有注意到许多以前的购房者抱怨的文化和阶级偏见。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3992, '2001考研英语', 'If it did, it would open up its diversity program, now focused narrowly on race and gender, and look for reporters who differ broadly by outlook, values, education, and class.', '如果这样做，它将开放其多样化项目，目前只关注种族和性别，并寻找在观点、价值观、教育和阶级上存在广泛差异的记者。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3993, '2001考研英语', 'What is the passage mainly about.', '这篇文章主要是关于什么的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3994, '2001考研英语', 'The process sweeps from hyperactive America to Europe and reaches the emerging countries with unsurpassed might.', '这一进程从过度活跃的美国蔓延到欧洲，并以前所未有的力量到达新兴国家。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (3995, '2001考研英语', '\" There\'s no question that the big are getting bigger and more powerful.', '“毫无疑问，大公司正变得越来越强大。');
