INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4185, '2003考研英语', 'Any threat of monopoly, they argue, is removed by fierce competition from trucks.', '他们认为，任何垄断威胁都会被卡车的激烈竞争所淘汰。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4186, '2003考研英语', 'But many shippers complain that for heavy bulk commodities traveling long distances, such as coal, chemicals, and grain, trucking is too costly and the railroads therefore have them by the throat.', '但是许多托运人抱怨说，对于长途运输的大宗商品，如煤炭、化学药品和谷物，卡车运输太昂贵了，因此铁路就把它们塞在喉咙里。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4187, '2003考研英语', 'The vast consolidation within the rail industry means that most shippers are served by only one rail company.', '铁路行业的大规模整合意味着大多数托运人只能由一家铁路公司服务。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4188, '2003考研英语', 'Shippers who feel they are being overcharged have the right to appeal to the federal government\'s Surface Transportation Board for rate relief, but the process is expensive, time consuming, and will work only in truly extreme cases.', '发货人觉得自己被多收了费用，有权向联邦政府水陆运输委员会请求减免运费，但是这个过程昂贵、耗时，而且只能在真正极端的情况下进行。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4189, '2003考研英语', 'Railroads justify rate discrimination against captive shippers on the grounds that in the long run it reduces everyone\'s cost.', '铁路公司对被指控的托运人实行歧视，理由是从长远来看，它降低了每个人的成本。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4190, '2003考研英语', 'If railroads charged all customers the same average rate, they argue, shippers who have the option of switching to trucks or other forms of transportation would do so, leaving remaining customers to shoulder the cost of keeping up the line.', '他们认为，如果铁路向所有客户收取相同的平均运费，那么选择改用卡车或其他运输方式的托运人就会这样做，剩下的客户将承担维持铁路运输的成本。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4191, '2003考研英语', 'It\'s theory to which many economists subscribe, but in practice it often leaves railroads in the position of determining which companies will flourish and which will fail.', '许多经济学家都赞同这一理论，但在实践中，它往往使铁路公司处于决定哪些公司会兴旺，哪些公司会倒闭的地位。');
