INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4982, '2009考研英语', 'I sincerely hope you will find these proposals useful.', '我真诚地希望你会发现这些建议是有用的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4983, '2009考研英语', 'Your prompt attention to my recommendations will be highly appreciated.', '如能迅速关注我的建议，将不胜感激。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4984, '2009考研英语', 'The caption in the drawing reads: \"the internet: near or far \".', '图中的标题写着：“互联网：近或远”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4985, '2009考研英语', 'The purpose of the drawing is to show us that the internet as a communication tool has both its advantages and disadvantages.', '这幅图的目的是告诉我们，互联网作为一种交流工具，既有优点也有缺点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4986, '2009考研英语', 'On the one hand, many people hold a view that internet makes us close than ever before.', '一方面，许多人认为互联网使我们比以往任何时候都亲密。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4987, '2009考研英语', 'With the development of science and technology, computers and internet are playing an increasingly important role in our daily lives.', '随着科学技术的发展，计算机和互联网在我们的日常生活中发挥着越来越重要的作用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4988, '2009考研英语', 'On the other hand, others argue that the internet weakens relationship among people.', '另一方面，另一些人则认为互联网削弱了人与人之间的关系。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4989, '2009考研英语', 'It can be easily spotted that some people may chat with total strangers online for hours, but may refuse to talk to their families or friends face to face for even a minute.', '很容易发现，有些人可能会在网上和完全陌生的人聊上几个小时，但可能会拒绝与家人或朋友面对面交谈一分钟。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4990, '2009考研英语', 'From what has been mentioned above, we may reasonably arrive at the conclusion that internet may draw us inches near, but could also set us oceans apart.', '从上面已经提到的，我们可以合理地得出结论，互联网可能把我们拉近几英寸，但也可能把我们海洋分开。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4991, '2009考研英语', 'Therefore, it is necessary for us to use internet in a reasonable way and take prompt initiatives to eliminate the negative effects concerned.', '因此，我们有必要合理使用互联网，及时采取措施消除其负面影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4992, '2009考研英语', 'Only in this way can we take advantage of internet and live in a more harmonious society.', '只有这样，我们才能利用互联网，生活在一个更加和谐的社会。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4993, '2009考研英语', 'Only in this way can we live in a more harmonious society.', '只有这样，我们才能生活在一个更加和谐的社会。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4994, '2010考研英语一', 'This suggests that the alleged \"Hawthorne effect\" is hard to pin down.', '这表明所谓的“霍桑效应”很难确定。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4995, '2010考研英语一', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEET 1.', '马克在答题纸1上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4996, '2010考研英语一', 'Theirs was a serious business, and even those reviewers who wore their learning lightly, like George Bernard Shaw and Ernest Newman, could be trusted to know what they were about.', '他们的工作很严肃，即使是像乔治·萧伯纳和欧内斯特·纽曼这样学识浅薄的评论家，也可以相信他们知道自己在做什么。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4997, '2010考研英语一', 'These men believed in journalism as a calling, and were proud to be published in the daily press.', '这些人相信新闻业是一种号召，并自豪地发表在《每日新闻》杂志上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4998, '2010考研英语一', 'Neville Cardus, who wrote for the Manchester Guardian from 1917 until shortly before his death in 1975, is now known solely as a writer of essays on the game of cricket.', '1917岁的Neville Cardus为1975岁的曼彻斯特卫报撰稿，直到现在才知道自己是板球游戏的作者。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (4999, '2010考研英语一', 'He was knighted in 1967, the first music critic to be so honored.', '他在1967被授予爵位，第一位音乐评论家是如此的荣幸。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5000, '2010考研英语一', 'Yet only one of his books is now in print, and his vast body of writings on music is unknown save to specialists.', '然而，他的一本书现在已经出版了，他在音乐方面的大量著作是未知的，留给专家们。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5001, '2010考研英语一', 'The prospect seems remote.', '前景似乎遥遥无期。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5002, '2010考研英语一', 'Journalistic tastes had changed long before his death, and postmodern readers have little use for the richly upholstered Vicwardian prose in which he specialized.', '在他去世之前很久，新闻品味就已经发生了变化，后现代读者对他所擅长的丰富多彩的维多瓦时期的散文几乎没有什么用处。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5003, '2010考研英语一', 'Moreover, the amateur tradition in music criticism has been in headlong retreat.', '此外，音乐批评中的业余传统也一直处于退步状态。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5004, '2010考研英语一', 'It is indicated in Paragraphs 1 and 2 that.', '第1款和第2款指出。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5005, '2010考研英语一', 'Newspaper reviews in England before World War II were characterized by.', '第二次世界大战前英国报纸评论的特点是：');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5006, '2010考研英语一', 'Which of the following would Shaw and Newman most probably agree on.', '肖和纽曼最有可能达成一致的是哪一个？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5007, '2010考研英语一', 'What can be learned about Cardus according to the last two paragraphs.', '根据最后两段，我们可以了解卡杜斯。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5008, '2010考研英语一', 'What would be the best title for the text.', '什么是最好的标题的文本。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5009, '2010考研英语一', 'Merrill Lynch got legal protection for an asset allocation strategy.', '美林对资产配置策略有法律保护。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5010, '2010考研英语一', 'One inventor patented a technique for lifting a box.', '一个发明家申请了一种提升箱子的技术。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5011, '2010考研英语一', 'In re Bilski, as the case is known , is \"a very big deal\", says Dennis D.', 'Dennis D.称，在Re Bilski中，这是一个“非常大的交易”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5012, '2010考研英语一', 'Crouch of the University of Missouri School of law.', '密苏里堪萨斯大学法学院的Crouch。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5013, '2010考研英语一', 'It \"has the potential to eliminate an entire class of patents.', '它有可能消除整个专利类别。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5014, '2010考研英语一', 'Later, move established companies raced to add such patents to their files, if only as a defensive move against rivals that might beat them to the punch.', '后来，一些老牌公司竞相将这些专利加入他们的档案，如果仅仅是为了对付那些可能击败他们的竞争对手。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5015, '2010考研英语一', 'Similarly, some Wall Street investment films armed themselves with patents for financial products, even as they took positions in court cases opposing the practice.', '类似地，一些华尔街投资电影也为自己的金融产品申请了专利，即使他们在反对这种做法的法庭案件中担任了职务。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5016, '2010考研英语一', 'The Bilski case involves a claimed patent on a method for hedging risk in the energy market.', 'Bilski案涉及在能源市场对冲风险的方法的专利申请。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5017, '2010考研英语一', 'The Federal circuit issued an unusual order stating that the case would be heard by all 12 of the court\'s judges, rather than a typical panel of three, and that one issue it wants to evaluate is whether it should \"reconsider\" its state street Bank ruling.', '联邦巡回法院发布了一项不同寻常的命令，规定该案件将由法院所有12名法官审理，而不是由3人组成的典型小组，并且它希望评估的一个问题是，它是否应该“重新考虑”其州立街道银行的裁决。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5018, '2010考研英语一', 'The Federal Circuit\'s action comes in the wake of a series of recent decisions by the supreme Court that has narrowed the scope of protections for patent holders.', '美国联邦巡回法院（FederalCir.）的诉讼是在最高法院最近做出一系列裁定之后作出的，这些裁定缩小了专利持有者的保护范围。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5019, '2010考研英语一', 'Last April, for example the justices signaled that too many patents were being upheld for \"inventions\" that are obvious.', '例如，去年四月，法官们表示，有太多的专利被“显而易见”的发明所支持。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5020, '2010考研英语一', 'Wegner, a patent attorney and professor at George Washington University Law School.', '韦格纳是乔治华盛顿大学法学院的专利代理人和教授。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5021, '2010考研英语一', 'Which of the following is true of the Bilski case.', 'Bilski案中的哪一个是正确的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5022, '2010考研英语一', 'Which of the following would be the subject of the text.', '下列哪一个将是正文的主题？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5023, '2010考研英语一', 'The idea is intuitively compelling, but it doesn\'t explain how ideas actually spread.', '这个想法直观地令人信服，但它不能解释思想究竟是如何传播的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5024, '2010考研英语一', 'The supposed importance of influentials derives from a plausible sounding but largely untested theory called the \"two step flow of communication\": Information flows from the media to the influentials and from them to everyone else.', '所谓影响力的重要性，源于一种听起来似乎有理，但基本上未经检验的理论，称为“两步传播流”：信息从媒体流向有影响力的人，并从他们流向其他人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5025, '2010考研英语一', 'The theory also seems to explain the sudden and unexpected popularity of certain looks, brands, or neighborhoods.', '这一理论似乎也解释了某些外表、品牌或邻里的突然和意外的流行。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5026, '2010考研英语一', 'In many such cases, a cursory search for causes finds that some small group of people was wearing, promoting, or developing whatever it is before anyone else paid attention.', '在许多这样的情况下，粗略地寻找原因会发现一小部分人在别人注意之前穿着、推销或开发任何东西。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5027, '2010考研英语一', 'In fact, they don\'t seem to be required of all.', '事实上，它们似乎并不需要。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5028, '2010考研英语一', 'The researchers\' argument stems from a simple observing about social influence, with the exception of a few celebrities like Oprah Winfrey—whose outsize presence is primarily a function of media, not interpersonal, influence—even the most influential memb', '研究人员的论点来自于对社会影响的简单观察，除了像奥普拉·温弗瑞这样的少数名人，他们的巨大影响力主要是媒体的作用，而不是人际关系，甚至是最有影响力的成员。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5029, '2010考研英语一', 'If people in the network just two degrees removed from the initial influential prove resistant, for example from the initial influential prove resistant, for example the cascade of change won\'t propagate very far or affect many people.', '如果人们在网络上刚从最初的两个影响力移除，证明抵抗，例如从最初有影响力的证明抵抗，例如级联的变化不会传播很远或影响很多人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5030, '2010考研英语一', 'They found that the principal requirement for what is called \"global cascades\"—the widespread propagation of influence through networks—is the presence not of a few influentials but, rather, of a critical mass of easily influenced people.', '他们发现，所谓的“全球级联”的主要要求是通过网络传播的广泛影响是不存在一些影响因素，而是一个受影响的人的关键群体。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5031, '2010考研英语一', 'By citing the book The Tipping Point, the author intends to.', '通过引用这本书的转折点，作者打算。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5032, '2010考研英语一', 'What the researchers have observed recently shows that.', '研究人员最近观察到的结果表明。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5033, '2010考研英语一', 'The underlined phrase \"these people\" in Paragraph 4 refers to the ones who.', '第4段中的下划线短语“这些人”指的是那些人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5034, '2010考研英语一', 'What is the essential element in the dynamics of social influence.', '社会影响的动态要素是什么？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5035, '2010考研英语一', 'Bankers have been blaming themselves for their troubles in public.', '银行家们一直把自己的烦恼归咎于公众。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5036, '2010考研英语一', 'Their rules, moan the banks, have forced them to report enormous losses, and it\'s just not fair.', '他们的规则，抱怨银行，迫使他们报告巨大的损失，这是不公平的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5037, '2010考研英语一', 'These rules say they must value some assets at the price a third party would pay, not the price managers and regulators would like them to fetch.', '这些规定说，他们必须以第三方愿意支付的价格对一些资产进行估值，而不是管理者和监管者希望他们索取的价格。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5038, '2010考研英语一', 'Unfortunately, banks\' lobbying now seems to be working.', '不幸的是，银行的游说现在似乎奏效了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5039, '2010考研英语一', 'And, unless banks carry toxic assets at prices that attract buyers, reviving the banking system will be difficult.', '而且，除非银行以吸引买家的价格输送有毒资产，否则复苏银行体系将是困难的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5040, '2010考研英语一', 'After a bruising encounter with Congress, America\'s Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB) rushed through rule changes.', '在经历了与国会的挫败之后，美国的财务会计准则委员会（FASB）匆忙地通过了规则变更。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5041, '2010考研英语一', 'Bob Herz, the FASB\'s chairman, cried out against those who \"question our motives.', 'FASB主席Bob Herz对那些质疑我们动机的人大喊大叫。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5042, '2010考研英语一', '\" Yet bank shares rose and the changes enhance what one lobby group politely calls \"the use of judgment by management.', '但银行股上涨，这些变化增强了游说团体所谓的“使用管理层的判断”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5043, '2010考研英语一', '\" European ministers instantly demanded that the International Accounting Standards Board (IASB) do likewise.', '欧洲部长们立即要求国际会计准则委员会（IASB）也这样做。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5044, '2010考研英语一', 'The IASB says it does not want to act without overall planning, but the pressure to fold when it completes it reconstruction of rules later this year is strong.', '国际会计准则理事会表示，它不想在没有总体规划的情况下采取行动，但今年晚些时候完成规则重建时要屈服的压力很大。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5045, '2010考研英语一', 'Charlie McCreevy, a European commissioner, warned the IASB that it did \"not live in a political vacuum\" but \"in the real word\" and that Europe could yet develop different rules.', '欧洲专员Charlie McCreevy警告IASB说，它没有“生活在政治真空中”，而是“真实的”，欧洲还可以制定不同的规则。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5046, '2010考研英语一', 'It was banks that were on the wrong planet, with accounts that vastly overvalued assets.', '银行是在错误的星球上，账目大大高估了资产。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5047, '2010考研英语一', 'Today they argue that market prices overstate losses, because they largely reflect the temporary illiquidity of markets, not the likely extent of bad debts.', '今天，他们认为市场价格夸大了损失，因为它们主要反映了市场的暂时流动性不足，而不是坏账的可能程度。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5048, '2010考研英语一', 'The truth will not be known for years.', '真相将数年不见。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5049, '2010考研英语一', 'But bank\'s shares trade below their book value, suggesting that investors are skeptical.', '但银行股价低于账面价值，这表明投资者对此持怀疑态度。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5050, '2010考研英语一', 'And dead markets partly reflect the paralysis of banks which will not sell assets for fear of booking losses, yet are reluctant to buy all those supposed bargains.', '市场死气沉沉，部分反映了银行陷入瘫痪，这些银行由于担心预订损失而不会出售资产，但又不愿购买所有那些所谓的便宜货。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5051, '2010考研英语一', 'To get the system working again, losses must be recognized and dealt with.', '要使系统再次工作，必须认识和处理损失。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5052, '2010考研英语一', 'America\'s new plan to buy up toxic assets will not work unless banks mark assets to levels which buyers find attractive.', '美国购买有毒资产的新计划将不起作用，除非银行将资产标记为买家认为有吸引力的水平。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5053, '2010考研英语一', 'The FASB and IASB have been exactly that, cleaning up rules on stock options and pensions, for example, against hostility from special interests.', '财务会计准则委员会和国际会计准则委员会就是这样，清理有关股票期权和养老金的规定，例如，反对来自特殊利益的敌意。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5054, '2010考研英语一', 'But by giving in to critics now they are inviting pressure to make more concessions.', '但现在向批评家屈服，他们正施压要求做出更多让步。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5055, '2010考研英语一', 'Bankers complained that they were forced to.', '银行家们抱怨说他们被迫。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5056, '2010考研英语一', 'According to the author, the rule changes of the FASB may result in.', '作者认为，FASB的规则变化可能导致。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5057, '2010考研英语一', 'The author thinks the banks were \"on the wrong planet\" in that they.', '作者认为银行是“错误的星球”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5058, '2010考研英语一', 'Paragraph E has been correctly placed.', 'E段被正确放置。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5059, '2010考研英语一', 'There is one paragraph which does not fit in with the text.', '有一段与课文不符。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5060, '2010考研英语一', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEET1.', '马克回答问题的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5061, '2010考研英语一', 'This development is boosting wholesale demand from the food service segment by 4 to 5 percent a year across Europe, compared with growth in retail demand of 1 to 2 percent.', '这一发展使整个欧洲食品服务部门的批发需求每年增长4%至5%，而零售需求增长1%至2%。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5062, '2010考研英语一', 'Meanwhile, as the recession is looming large, people are getting anxious.', '与此同时，随着经济衰退即将来临，人们开始焦虑起来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5063, '2010考研英语一', 'They tend to keep a tighter hold on their purse and consider eating at home a realistic alternative.', '他们倾向于更严格地控制自己的钱包，并考虑在家吃饭是一种现实的选择。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5064, '2010考研英语一', 'But almost all have ignored the big, profitable opportunity in their own backyard: the wholesale food and drink trade, which appears to be just the kind of market retailers need.', '但是，几乎所有人都忽略了自己后院中赚钱的大好机会：批发食品和饮料贸易，这似乎正是市场零售商所需要的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5065, '2010考研英语一', 'The functioning of the market is based on flexible trends dominated by potential buyers.', '市场的运作是基于潜在买家主导的灵活趋势。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5066, '2010考研英语一', 'In other words, it is up to the buyer, rather than the seller, to decide what to buy.', '换句话说，决定买什么的是买方，而不是卖方。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5067, '2010考研英语一', 'Retailers that master the intricacies of wholesaling in Europe may well expect to rake in substantial profits thereby.', '精通欧洲批发业务的零售商很可能会因此获得巨额利润。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5068, '2010考研英语一', 'At least, that is how it looks as a whole.', '至少，这是一个整体。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5069, '2010考研英语一', 'Closer inspection reveals important differences among the biggest national markets, especially in their customer segments and wholesale structures, as well as the competitive dynamics of individual food and drink categories.', '更仔细的检查揭示了最大的国家市场之间的重要差异，特别是在其客户细分和批发结构方面，以及单个食品和饮料类别的竞争动态。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5070, '2010考研英语一', 'Big retailers must understand these differences before they can identify the segments of European wholesaling in which their particular abilities might unseat smaller but entrenched competitors.', '大型零售商必须了解这些差异，才能识别出欧洲批发业的哪些细分市场，在这些细分市场中，他们的特殊能力可能击败规模较小但根深蒂固的竞争对手。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5071, '2010考研英语一', 'New skills and unfamiliar business models are needed too.', '也需要新的技能和不熟悉的商业模式。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5072, '2010考研英语一', 'Such food service operators range from snack machines to large institutional catering ventures, but most of these businesses are known in the trade as \"horeca\": hotels, restaurants, and cafes.', '这类食品服务运营商的范围从快餐机到大型机构餐饮企业，但这些行业中的大多数业务被称为“horeca”：酒店、餐馆和咖啡馆。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5073, '2010考研英语一', 'Overall, Europe\'s wholesale market for food and drink is growing at the same sluggish pace as the retail market, but the figures, when added together, mask two opposing trends.', '总体而言，欧洲的食品和饮料批发市场以零售市场同样缓慢的速度增长，但这些数据加在一起掩盖了两种相反的趋势。');
