INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5275, '2011考研英语一', '\" But 1 some claims to the contrary, laughing probably has little influence on physical fitness.', '但1的人则相反，笑对身体健康的影响很小。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5276, '2011考研英语一', 'But because hard laughter is difficult to 4 , a good laugh is unlikely to have 5 benefits the way, say, walking or jogging does.', '但是因为笑很难达到4，好的笑不可能有5的好处，比如走路或慢跑。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5277, '2011考研英语一', '6 , instead of straining muscles to build them, as exercise does, laughter apparently accomplishes the 7.', '6，代替锻炼肌肉，锻炼身体，笑显然能达到7。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5278, '2011考研英语一', 'Such bodily reaction might conceivably help 9 the effects of psychological stress.', '这样的身体反应可能有助于9心理压力的影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5279, '2011考研英语一', '11 one classical theory of emotion, our feelings are partially rooted 12 physical reactions.', '11一个经典的情感理论，我们的感情部分地植根于12个物理反应。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5280, '2011考研英语一', 'It was argued at the end of the 19th century that humans do not cry 13 they are sad but that they become sad when the tears begin to flow.', '19世纪末有人提出，人类不是哭，而是在眼泪开始流出时变得悲伤。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5281, '2011考研英语一', 'Although sadness also 14 tears, evidence suggests that emotions can flow 15 muscular responses.', '尽管悲伤也有14个眼泪，但证据表明，情感可以流出15个肌肉反应。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5282, '2011考研英语一', 'Those forced to exercise their smiling muscles 18 more enthusiastically to funny cartoons than did those whose mouths were contracted in a frown, 19 that expressions may influence emotions rather than just the other way around.', '那些被迫对有趣的卡通片更加热情地锻炼微笑的肌肉的人比那些皱着眉头的人更热情，19那些表情可能影响情绪，而不只是反过来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5283, '2011考研英语一', 'Answer the questions below each text by choosing A, B, C or D.', '通过选择A、B、C或D回答每个文本下面的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5284, '2011考研英语一', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEET 1.', '马克在答题纸1上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5285, '2011考研英语一', 'For the most part, the response has been favorable, to say the least.', '至少在大多数情况下，反应是有利的，至少可以说。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5286, '2011考研英语一', 'One of the reasons why the appointment came as such a surprise, however, is that Gilbert is comparatively little known.', '然而，任命的原因之一是吉尔伯特的知名度相对较低。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5287, '2011考研英语一', '\" As a description of the next music director of an orchestra that has hitherto been led by musicians like Gustav Mahler and Pierre Boulez, that seems likely to have struck at least some Times readers as faint praise.', '作为对迄今为止由古斯塔夫·马勒和皮埃尔·布莱兹等音乐家领导的管弦乐队的下一位音乐总监的描述，这似乎使至少一些《泰晤士报》的读者印象深刻，认为该管弦乐队受到了微弱的赞扬。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5288, '2011考研英语一', 'For my part, I have no idea whether Gilbert is a great conductor or even a good one.', '就我而言，我不知道吉尔伯特是一个伟大的指挥家，甚至是一个好的指挥家。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5289, '2011考研英语一', 'To be sure, he performs an impressive variety of interesting compositions, but it is not necessary for me to visit Avery Fisher Hall, or anywhere else, to hear interesting orchestral music.', '当然，他演奏了各种令人印象深刻的有意思的作品，但对我来说，没有必要去艾弗里·费希尔大厅或其他地方听有趣的管弦乐。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5290, '2011考研英语一', 'All I have to do is to go to my CD shelf, or boot up my computer and download still more recorded music from iTunes.', '我所要做的就是去我的CD架，或者启动我的电脑，从iTunes下载更多的录音音乐。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5291, '2011考研英语一', 'Devoted concertgoers who reply that recordings are no substitute for live performance are missing the point.', '那些认为录音不能代替现场表演的忠实的演唱者们忽略了这一点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5292, '2011考研英语一', 'The widespread availability of such recordings has thus brought about a crisis in the institution of the traditional classical concert.', '这种录音的广泛使用给传统古典音乐会的制度带来了危机。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5293, '2011考研英语一', '\" But what will be the nature of that difference.', '“但这种差异的本质是什么呢？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5294, '2011考研英语一', 'According to the text, which of the following is true of recordings.', '根据文本，下列哪一个是真实的录音。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5295, '2011考研英语一', 'When Liam McGee departed as president of Bank of America in August, his explanation was surprisingly straight up.', 'Liam McGee于8月份辞去美国银行行长职务时，他的解释出人意料地直截了当。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5296, '2011考研英语一', 'Rather than cloaking his exit in the usual vague excuses, he came right out and said he was leaving \"to pursue my goal of running a company.', '他没有用通常模棱两可的借口来掩饰他的离职，而是直接说出来，说他要离开“是为了追求我经营公司的目标”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5297, '2011考研英语一', '\" Broadcasting his ambition was \"very much my decision,\" McGee says.', 'McGee说：“广播他的野心是我的决定。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5298, '2011考研英语一', 'Within two weeks, he was talking for the first time with the board of Hartford Financial Services Group, which named him CEO and chairman on September 29.', '两周之内，他首次与哈特福德金融服务集团（Hartford Financial Services Group）董事会进行了交谈，该集团于9月29日任命他为首席执行官和董事长。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5299, '2011考研英语一', 'It also sent a clear message to the outside world about his aspirations.', '它还向外界传达了一个明确的愿望。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5300, '2011考研英语一', 'In recent weeks the No.', '最近几周没有。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5301, '2011考研英语一', '2 executives at Avon and American Express quit with the explanation that they were looking for a CEO post.', '雅芳和美国运通公司的2位高管辞职，理由是他们在寻找CEO职位。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5302, '2011考研英语一', 'A turbulent business environment also has senior managers cautious of letting vague pronouncements cloud their reputations.', '动荡的商业环境也让高层管理者谨慎地让含糊其辞的声明掩盖了他们的声誉。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5303, '2011考研英语一', 'As the first signs of recovery begin to take hold, deputy chiefs may be more willing to make the jump without a net.', '随着复苏的最初迹象开始出现，副总经理可能更愿意无网跳伞。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5304, '2011考研英语一', 'In the third quarter, CEO turnover was down 23% from a year ago as nervous boards stuck with the leaders they had, according to Liberum Research.', '根据.umResearch的数据，第三季度，CEO的营业额比去年同期下降了23%，因为紧张的董事会会紧紧抓住他们的领导人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5305, '2011考研英语一', 'As the economy picks up, opportunities will abound for aspiring leaders.', '随着经济的复苏，有抱负的领导人会有很多机会。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5306, '2011考研英语一', 'The decision to quit a senior position to look for a better one is unconventional.', '离开高级职位去寻找一个更好的职位的决定是非常规的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5307, '2011考研英语一', 'For years executives and headhunters have adhered to the rule that the most attractive CEO candidates are the ones who must be poached.', '多年来，高管和猎头公司一直坚持这样的原则，即最有吸引力的CEO候选人就是那些必须被挖走的人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5308, '2011考研英语一', 'Ellen Marram quit as chief of Tropicana a decade ago, saying she wanted to be a CEO.', 'Ellen Marram十年前辞去了TrPopina首席执行官的职务，她说她想成为一名首席执行官。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5309, '2011考研英语一', 'He finally took that post at a major financial institution three years later.', '三年后，他终于在一家大型金融机构接受了这个职位。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5310, '2011考研英语一', 'Many recruiters say the old disgrace is fading for top performers.', '许多招聘人员说，表演者的老耻辱正在逐渐消失。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5311, '2011考研英语一', 'The financial crisis has made it more acceptable to be between jobs or to leave a bad one.', '金融危机使人们更容易接受工作或离职。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5312, '2011考研英语一', 'Which of the following is the best title for the text.', '以下哪一个是最佳的文本标题？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5313, '2011考研英语一', 'Paid and owned media are controlled by marketers promoting their own products.', '付费媒体和自有媒体由营销人员推销自己的产品来控制。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5314, '2011考研英语一', 'This trend, which we believe is still in its infancy, effectively began with retailers and travel providers such as airlines and hotels and will no doubt go further.', '我们认为，这种趋势还处于初期阶段，实际上始于零售商和旅行社，如航空公司和酒店，并且无疑将进一步发展。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5315, '2011考研英语一', 'The same dramatic technological changes that have provided marketers with more (and more diverse) communications choices have also increased the risk that passionate consumers will voice their opinions in quicker, more visible, and much more damaging ways', '同样的戏剧性的技术变化为营销者提供了更多（和更多样化的）沟通选择，也增加了充满激情的消费者以更快、更明显、更具破坏性的方式表达自己观点的风险。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5316, '2011考研英语一', 'Such hijacked media are the opposite of earned media: an asset or campaign becomes hostage to consumers, other stakeholders, or activists who make negative allegations about a brand or product.', '这种被劫持的媒体与赚钱的媒体截然相反：资产或活动成为消费者、其他利益相关者或活动家的人质，他们对品牌或产品提出负面指控。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5317, '2011考研英语一', 'Members of social networks, for instance, are learning that they can hijack media to apply pressure on the businesses that originally created them.', '例如，社交网络的成员正在学习他们可以劫持媒体来对最初创建它们的企业施加压力。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5318, '2011考研英语一', 'If that happens, passionate consumers would try to persuade others to boycott products, putting the reputation of the target company at risk.', '如果出现这种情况，热情的消费者会试图说服其他人抵制产品，从而将目标公司的声誉置于危险之中。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5319, '2011考研英语一', 'Which of the following is the text mainly about.', '以下是本文的主要内容。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5320, '2011考研英语一', 'Of course, the image of parenthood that celebrity magazines like Us Weekly and People present is hugely unrealistic, especially when the parents are single mothers like Bullock.', '当然，像《我们周刊》和《人物》这样的名人杂志所展现的为人父母的形象非常不现实，尤其是当父母是像布洛克这样的单身母亲时。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5321, '2011考研英语一', 'According to several studies concluding that parents are less happy than childless couples, single parents are the least happy of all.', '根据一些研究得出的结论是，父母比没有孩子的夫妇更不快乐，单亲父母是最不快乐的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5322, '2011考研英语一', 'Which of the following can be inferred from the last paragraph.', '下列哪一个可以从最后一段推断出来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5323, '2011考研英语一', 'Part B Directions: The following paragraphs are given in a wrong order.', '第二部分：按错误的顺序给出下列段落。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5324, '2011考研英语一', 'Paragraphs E and G have been correctly placed.', '段落E和G已被正确放置。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5325, '2011考研英语一', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEET 1.', '马克在答题纸1上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5326, '2011考研英语一', 'You can, Mr Menand points out, become a lawyer in three years and a medical doctor in four.', 'Menand先生指出，你可以在三年内成为一名律师，四年成为一名医生。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5327, '2011考研英语一', 'But the regular time it takes to get a doctoral degree in the humanities is nine years.', '但是获得人文学科博士学位需要的时间是九年。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5328, '2011考研英语一', 'Not surprisingly, up to half of all doctoral students in English drop out before getting their degrees.', '不足为奇的是，多达一半的英语博士生在拿到学位之前辍学。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5329, '2011考研英语一', 'These are disciplines that are going out of style: 22% of American college graduates now major in business compared with only 2% in history and 4% in English.', '这些学科已经过时了：22%的美国大学毕业生现在主修商业，而历史专业只有2%，英语专业只有4%。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5330, '2011考研英语一', 'However, many leading American universities want their undergraduates to have a grounding in the basic canon of ideas that every educated person should possess.', '然而，许多顶尖的美国大学希望他们的本科生有一个基础的思想，每个受过教育的人应该拥有。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5331, '2011考研英语一', 'But most find it difficult to agree on what a \"general education\" should look like.', '但大多数人很难就“普通教育”应该是什么样子达成一致意见。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5332, '2011考研英语一', 'There are simply too few posts.', '职位太少了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5333, '2011考研英语一', 'This is partly because universities continue to produce ever more PhDs.', '部分原因是大学继续生产更多的博士学位。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5334, '2011考研英语一', 'Fewer students require fewer teachers.', '更少的学生需要更少的教师。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5335, '2011考研英语一', 'Many students experience both varieties.', '许多学生都经历过这两种变种。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5336, '2011考研英语一', 'Professionalism has turned the acquisition of a doctoral degree into a prerequisite for a successful academic career: as late as 1969 a third of American professors did not possess one.', '专业主义已经把获得博士学位变成了成功的学术生涯的先决条件：直到1969年，三分之一的美国教授都没有博士学位。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5337, '2011考研英语一', '\" So disciplines acquire a monopoly not just over the production of knowledge, but also over the production of the producers of knowledge.', '因此，学科不仅垄断了知识的生产，而且垄断了知识的生产者。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5338, '2011考研英语一', '\" Otherwise, academics will continue to think dangerously alike, increasingly detached from the societies which they study, investigate and criticise.', '否则，学者们会继续危险地进行同样的思考，越来越脱离他们所研究、调查和批评的社会。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5339, '2011考研英语一', '\"Academic inquiry, at least in some fields, may need to become less exclusionary and more holistic.', '“学术调查，至少在某些领域，可能需要变得不那么排斥和更全面。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5340, '2011考研英语一', '\" Yet quite how that happens, Mr Menand does not say.', '“但这是如何发生的，”Menand先生没有这么说。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5341, '2011考研英语一', 'They may then decide to go elsewhere.', '然后他们可能决定去别处。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5342, '2011考研英语一', 'For something curious has been happening in American universities, and Louis Menand, a professor of English at Harvard University, captured it skillfully.', '在美国大学里发生了一些奇怪的事情，哈佛大学的英语教授Louis Menand巧妙地抓住了它。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5343, '2011考研英语一', 'Part C Directions: Read the following text carefully and then translate the underlined segments into Chinese.', 'C部分：仔细阅读下面的文字，然后将下划线段翻译成中文。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5344, '2011考研英语一', 'Your translation should be written clearly on ANSWER SHEET 2.', '你的翻译应该清楚地写在答题纸2上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5345, '2011考研英语一', 'However, Allen believed that the unconscious mind generates as much action as the conscious mind, and (47)while we may be able to sustain the illusion of control through the conscious mind alone, in reality we are continually faced with a question: \"Why c', '然而，艾伦相信无意识头脑产生的行动与有意识头脑产生的行动一样多，并且（47）虽然我们可能仅通过有意识头脑就能维持控制的幻觉，但实际上我们仍然面临着一个问题：“为什么c.');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5346, '2011考研英语一', '\" Since desire and will are damaged by the presence of thoughts that do not accord with desire, Allen concluded: \"We do not attract what we want, but what we are.', '由于欲望和意志被与欲望不一致的思想的存在所破坏，艾伦总结道：“我们不吸引我们想要的东西，而是吸引我们自己。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5347, '2011考研英语一', 'There is no gap between mind and matter.', '思想和物质之间没有差距。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5348, '2011考研英语一', '\" (48) This seems a justification for neglect of those in need, and a rationalization of exploitation, of the superiority of those at the top and the inferiority of those at the bottom.', '“（48）这似乎是忽视那些需要帮助的人的理由，是合理化剥削、上层阶级的优越性和底层人的劣势。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5349, '2011考研英语一', 'Each set of circumstances, however bad, offers a unique opportunity for growth.', '每一种情况，无论多么糟糕，都为增长提供了一个独特的机会。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5350, '2011考研英语一', 'If circumstances always determined the life and prospects of people, then humanity would never have progressed.', '如果环境总是决定着人们的生活和前途，那么人类就永远不会进步。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5351, '2011考研英语一', 'Section III Writing Part A 51.', '第三部分，第51部分。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5352, '2011考研英语一', 'Directions: Write a letter to a friend of yours to 1) recommend one of your favorite movies and 2) give reasons for your recommendation.', '说明：给你的朋友写封信，1）推荐你最喜欢的电影之一，2）给出推荐的理由。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5353, '2011考研英语一', 'Do not sign your own name at the end of the letter.', '不要在信的末尾签上自己的名字。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5354, '2011考研英语一', 'Use \"Li Ming\" instead.', '用“李明”代替。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5355, '2011考研英语一', 'Do not write the address.', '不要写地址。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5356, '2011考研英语一', 'In your essay, you should 1) describe the drawing briefly, 2) explain its intended meaning, and 3) give your comments.', '在你的文章中，你应该1）简单地描述这幅画，2）解释它的意图，3）给出你的评论。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5357, '2011考研英语一', 'You should write neatly on ANSWER SHEET 2.', '你应该整洁地写在答题纸2上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5358, '2011考研英语一', 'As a description of the next music director of an orchestra that hashitherto been led by musicians like Gustav Mahler and Pierre Boulez, that seems likely to have struck at least someTimesreaders as faint praise.', '作为对迄今为止一直由古斯塔夫·马勒和皮埃尔·布莱兹等音乐家领导的管弦乐队的下一位音乐总监的描述，《纽约时报》的读者们似乎至少会觉得这有点夸奖。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5359, '2011考研英语一', 'Within two weeks, he was talking for the first time with the board of Hartford Financial Services Group, which named him CEO and chairman on September 29.', '两周之内，他首次与哈特福德金融服务集团（Hartford Financial Services Group）董事会进行了交谈，该集团于9月29日任命他为首席执行官和董事长。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5360, '2011考研英语一', 'For years executives and headhunters have adhered to the rule that the most attractive CEO candidates are the ones who must bepoached.', '多年来，高管和猎头一直坚持这样的规则：最有吸引力的CEO候选人是那些必须被偷窃的人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5361, '2011考研英语一', 'The same dramatic technological changes that have provided marketers with more (and more diverse) communications choices have also increased the risk that passionate consumers will voice their opinions in quicker, more visible, and much more damaging ways', '同样的戏剧性的技术变化为营销者提供了更多（和更多样化的）沟通选择，也增加了充满激情的消费者以更快、更明显、更具破坏性的方式表达自己观点的风险。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5362, '2011考研英语一', 'Or so everyone keeps saying.', '或者每个人都这么说。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5363, '2011考研英语一', '47) While we may be able to sustain the illusion of control through the conscious mind alone, in reality we are continually faced with a question: \"Why cannot I make myself do this or achieve that.', '47)虽然我们可能仅仅通过有意识的头脑就能维持控制幻觉，但实际上，我们不断面临一个问题：“为什么我不能让自己做到这一点或做到这一点？”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5364, '2011考研英语一', '48) This seems a justification for neglect of those in need, and a rationalization of exploitation, of the superiority of those at the top and the inferiority of those at the bottom.', '这似乎是忽视那些有需要的人的理由，也是剥削、上层人的优势和下层人的劣势的合理化。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5365, '2011考研英语一', '49) circumstances seem to be designed to bring out the best in us, and if we feel that we have been \"wronged\" then we are unlikely to begin a conscious effort to escape from our situation.', '环境似乎是为了展现我们最好的一面而设计的，如果我们觉得自己被“冤枉”了，那么我们就不太可能开始有意识地努力摆脱我们的处境。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5366, '2011考研英语一', 'For one thing, the beautiful language in this original English movie may contribute to your study of English in listening, speaking, reading and writing.', '首先，这部原版英文电影中的优美语言可能有助于你在听、说、读、写方面的英语学习。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5367, '2011考研英语一', 'For another thing, the profound cultural elements implicit in the scene will equip you with foreign cultural background and, above all, enrich your daily life.', '另一方面，场景中蕴含的深厚的文化元素将为您提供外国文化背景，最重要的是，丰富您的日常生活。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5368, '2011考研英语一', 'Would you like to see this movie after my recommendation.', '在我推荐之后，你愿意看这部电影吗？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5369, '2011考研英语一', 'Remember to tell me your opinion about the movie.', '记得告诉我你对这部电影的看法。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5370, '2011考研英语一', 'I am looking forward to your early reply.', '我期待着您的早日答复。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5371, '2011考研英语一', 'The picture illustrates that two tourists are chatting and eating happily on a boat and casually throwing their rubbish into the lake which is full of litter and waste.', '图为两名游客在船上聊天、吃得很开心，随便把垃圾扔到满是垃圾和废物的湖里。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5372, '2011考研英语一', 'Why does this phenomenon arise.', '为什么会出现这种现象呢？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5373, '2011考研英语一', 'Many factors are accounting for it.', '许多因素是它的罪魁祸首。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5374, '2011考研英语一', 'First and foremost, to some people, the consciousness of protecting environment is still not so strong.', '首先，对一些人来说，保护环境的意识还不太强。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5375, '2011考研英语一', 'They may not think it is a big deal to throw rubbish everywhere.', '他们可能不认为到处乱扔垃圾是一件大事。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5376, '2011考研英语一', 'From what has been discussed above, it is urgent to take some effective and relative measures.', '从以上讨论中，迫切需要采取有效的措施。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5377, '2011考研英语一', 'In the first place, we should continue to conduct more propaganda in communities and schools so as to let people realize the importance of protecting environment.', '首先，我们应该在社区和学校继续进行更多的宣传，让人们认识到保护环境的重要性。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5378, '2011考研英语一', 'In the second, more rules should be made and carried out by the government to restrain the conduction of destroying environment.', '第二，政府应制定更多的规章制度，制止破坏环境的行为。');
