INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5452, '2011考研英语二', 'Will the European Union make it.', '欧盟会成功吗？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5453, '2011考研英语二', 'The question would have sounded strange not long ago.', '这个问题不久前听起来就很奇怪了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5454, '2011考研英语二', 'As well as those chronic problems, the EU faces an acute crisis in its economic core, the 16 countries that use the single currency.', '除了那些长期存在的问题，欧盟还面临着其经济核心的严重危机，即16个使用单一货币的国家。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5455, '2011考研英语二', 'Translated, that means politicians intervening in monetary policy and a system of redistribution from richer to poorer members, via cheaper borrowing for governments through common Eurobonds or complete fiscal transfers.', '换言之，这意味着政客们通过共同发行的欧洲债券或完成财政转移来干预货币政策和从较富裕的成员国向较贫穷的成员国的再分配制度，为各国政府提供更便宜的借贷。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5456, '2011考研英语二', 'It is too soon to write off the EU.', '现在注销欧盟还为时过早。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5457, '2011考研英语二', 'At its best, the European project is remarkably liberal: built around a single market of 27 rich and poor countries, its internal borders are far more open to goods, capital and labour than any comparable trading area.', '在最好的情况下，欧洲项目是非常自由的：围绕着由27个富国和穷国组成的单一市场建设，其内部边界对货物、资本和劳动力的开放程度远远高于任何可比贸易区。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5458, '2011考研英语二', 'It is an ambitious attempt to blunt the sharpest edges of globalization, and make capitalism benign.', '这是一个雄心勃勃的尝试，打破全球化最尖锐的边缘，使资本主义变得良性。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5459, '2011考研英语二', 'The EU is faced with so many problems that.', '欧盟面临着如此多的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5460, '2011考研英语二', 'To solve the euro problem, Germany proposed that.', '为了解决欧元问题，德国提出了这一点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5461, '2011考研英语二', 'There are two extra headings that you do not need to use.', '有两个额外的标题，你不需要使用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5462, '2011考研英语二', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEET 1.', '马克在答题纸1上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5463, '2011考研英语二', 'The demands follow comments last week by the health secretary, Andrew Lansley, who insisted the government could not force people to make healthy choices and promised to free businesses from public health regulations.', '这些要求是在卫生部长安德鲁·兰斯利（Andrew Lansley）上周发表评论之后提出的，他坚称政府不能强迫人们做出健康的选择，并承诺将企业从公共卫生条例中解放出来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5464, '2011考研英语二', 'They argue that government action is necessary to curb Britain\'s addiction to unhealthy food and help halt spiraling rates of obesity, diabetes and heart disease.', '他们认为，政府的行动是必要的，以遏制英国对不健康食品的成瘾，并帮助遏制肥胖，糖尿病和心脏病的螺旋上升率。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5465, '2011考研英语二', 'Professor Terence Stephenson, president of the Royal College of Paediatrics and Child Health, said that the consumption of unhealthy food should be seen to be just as damaging as smoking or binge drinking.', '英国皇家儿科和儿童健康学院院长泰伦斯·斯蒂芬森教授说，不健康食品的消费应该被视为与吸烟或酗酒一样有害。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5466, '2011考研英语二', '\"Thirty years ago, it would have been inconceivable to have imagined a ban on smoking in the workplace or in pubs, and yet that is what we have now.', '“30年前，想像禁止在工作场所或酒吧抽烟是难以想象的，然而现在我们已经做到了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5467, '2011考研英语二', 'Are we willing to be just as courageous in respect of obesity.', '我们是否愿意在肥胖方面勇敢一点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5468, '2011考研英语二', 'I would suggest that we should be,\" said the leader of the UK\'s children\'s doctors.', '“我建议我们应该这样做，”英国儿童医生的领导人说。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5469, '2011考研英语二', 'Lansley has alarmed health campaigners by suggesting he wants industry rather than government to take the lead.', 'Lansley警告健康倡导者，他希望工业而不是政府带头。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5470, '2011考研英语二', 'He said that manufacturers of crisps and confectionery could play a central role in the Change4Life campaign, the centrepiece of government efforts to boost healthy eating and fitness.', '他说，薯片和糖果制造商可以在Change4Life运动中发挥中心作用。Change4Life运动是政府努力促进健康饮食和健身的中心内容。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5471, '2011考研英语二', 'Stephenson suggested potential restrictions could include banning TV advertisements for foods high in fat, salt or sugar before the 9pm watershed and limiting them on billboards or in cinemas.', '斯蒂芬森建议可能的限制措施包括在晚上9点前禁止电视广告中高脂肪、高盐和高糖的食物，并限制广告牌或电影院播放。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5472, '2011考研英语二', 'Such a move could affect firms such as McDonald\'s, which sponsors the youth coaching scheme run by the Football Association.', '这一举措可能会影响麦当劳等公司，该公司赞助由足球协会经营的青年教练计划。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5473, '2011考研英语二', 'Professor Dinesh Bhugra, president of the Royal College of Psychiatrists, said: \"If children are taught about the impact that food has on their growth, and that some things can harm, at least information is available up front.', '皇家精神病学院院长Dinesh Bhugra教授说：“如果孩子们被告知食物对他们生长的影响，以及一些东西会伤害，至少信息是可以得到的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5474, '2011考研英语二', 'A Department of Health spokesperson said: \"We need to create a new vision for public health where all of society works together to get healthy and live longer.', '卫生部的一位发言人说：“我们需要为公共卫生创造一个新的愿景，在这个愿景中，全社会共同努力，使健康长寿。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5475, '2011考研英语二', 'This includes creating a new \'responsibility deal\' with business, built on social responsibility, not state regulation.', '这包括建立一个新的“责任交易”，建立在社会责任之上，而不是国家监管。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5476, '2011考研英语二', 'Later this year, we will publish a white paper setting out exactly how we will achieve this.', '今年晚些时候，我们将公布一份白皮书，明确指出我们将如何实现这一目标。');
