INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5495, '2011考研英语二', 'Even American newspapers, which inhabit the most troubled come of the global industry, have not only survived but often returned to profit.', '即使是美国报纸，它栖息于最麻烦的来自全球产业，不仅幸存下来，而且经常恢复盈利。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5496, '2011考研英语二', 'The whirlwind that swept through newsrooms harmed everybody, but much of the damage has been concentrated in areas where newspapers are least distinctive.', '席卷新闻编辑室的旋风伤害了每一个人，但是大部分的伤害集中在报纸最没有特色的地方。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5497, '2011考研英语二', 'We tend to think of the decades immediately following World War II as a time of prosperity and growth, with soldiers returning home by the millions, going off to college on the G.', '我们倾向于把二战后紧接着的几十年看作是一个繁荣和发展的时代，数以百万计的士兵返回家园，在G.');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5498, '2011考研英语二', 'Bill and lining up at the marriage bureaus.', '比尔在婚姻局排队等候。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5499, '2011考研英语二', 'In his Case Study House, Ralph Rapson may have mispredicted just how mechanical revolution would impact everyday life—few American families acquired helicopters, though most eventually got clothes dryers —but his belief that selfsufficiency was both desir', '在他的案例研究所，Ralph Rapson可能错误地预测了机械革命将如何影响日常生活，很少有美国家庭获得直升飞机，尽管大多数人最终得到了衣物干燥器——但他相信自给自足是德雷尔。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5500, '2011考研英语二', 'Leading doctors today weigh in on the debate over the government\'s role in promoting public health by demanding that ministers impose \"fat taxes\" on unhealthy food and introduce cigarettestyle warnings to children about the dangers of a poor diet.', '今天，一些顶尖的医生就政府在促进公共卫生方面的作用展开了辩论，他们要求部长们对不健康的食品征收“脂肪税”，并向儿童提出关于不良饮食危险的香烟睾丸警告。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5501, '2011考研英语二', '\"Thirty years ago, it would have been inconceivable to have imagined a ban on smoking in the workplace or in pubs, and yet that is what we have now.', '“30年前，想像禁止在工作场所或酒吧抽烟是难以想象的，然而现在我们已经做到了。');
