INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5534, '2012考研英语一', 'That whispered message, halfinvitation and half forcing, is what most of us think of when we hear the wordspeer pressure.', '当我们听到单词的压力时，大多数人都会想到这种低语、半音效和半强迫。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5535, '2012考研英语一', 'It usually leads to no good — drinking, drugs and casual sex.', '它通常导致没有良好的饮酒、毒品和随意的性行为。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5536, '2012考研英语一', 'But in her new book Join the Club, Tina Rosenberg contends that peer pressure can also be a positive force through what she calls the social cure, in which organizations and officials use the power of group dynamics to help individuals improve their lives', '但是在她的新书《加入俱乐部》中，蒂娜·罗森博格认为，同龄人的压力也可以通过她称之为社会治愈的一种积极力量，在这种社会治愈中，组织和官员利用群体动力学的力量来帮助个人改善他们的生活。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5537, '2012考研英语一', 'The idea seems promising,and Rosenberg is a perceptive observer.', '这个想法似乎是有希望的，罗森伯格是一个敏锐的观察者。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5538, '2012考研英语一', 'But on the general effectiveness of the social cure, Rosenberg is less persuasive.', '但就社会治疗的一般效果而言，罗森伯格没有那么有说服力。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5539, '2012考研英语一', 'Join the Club is filled with too much irrelevant detail and not enough exploration of the social and biological factors that make peer pressure so powerful.', '加入这个俱乐部充满了太多的无关的细节，而没有充分挖掘社会因素和生物因素，使得同龄人压力如此强大。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5540, '2012考研英语一', 'Rage Against the Haze failed once state funding was cut.', '一旦国家资金被削减，对雾霾的愤怒就失败了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5541, '2012考研英语一', 'Evidence that the loveLife program produces lasting changes is limited and mixed.', '证据表明，爱情生活计划产生持久的变化是有限的和混合的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5542, '2012考研英语一', 'An emerging body of research shows that positive health habits — as well as negative ones — spread through networks of friends via social communication.', '一项新兴的研究表明，积极的健康习惯——以及消极的——通过社交网络传播给朋友。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5543, '2012考研英语一', 'This is a subtle form of peer pressure: we unconsciously imitate the behavior we see every day.', '这是一种微妙的同伴压力：我们不知不觉地模仿我们每天看到的行为。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5544, '2012考研英语一', 'Far less certain, however, is how successfully experts and bureaucrats can select our peer groups and steer their activities in virtuous directions.', '然而，更不确定的是，专家和官僚如何能够成功地选择我们的同行团体，并引导他们的活动向着良好的方向发展。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5545, '2012考研英语一', 'The tactic never really works.', '这种战术从来都不奏效。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5546, '2012考研英语一', 'The company, a major energy supplier in New England, provoked justified outrage in Vermont last week when it announced it wasreneging on a longstanding commitment to abide by the strict nuclear regulations.', '这家新英格兰的主要能源供应商上周在佛蒙特州宣布，它违背了遵守严格核法规的长期承诺，这激起了人们义愤填膺。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5547, '2012考研英语一', 'Then, too, the company went along.', '然后，公司也跟着去了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5548, '2012考研英语一', 'Certainly, there are valid concerns about the patchwork regulations that could result if every state sets its own rules.', '当然，如果每一个州制定了自己的规则，都有可能对修补条例产生有效的担忧。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5549, '2012考研英语一', 'But had Entergy kept its word, that debate would be beside the point.', '但如果伊恩坚持自己的话，那场辩论就离题了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5550, '2012考研英语一', 'The company seems to have concluded that its reputation in Vermont is already so damaged that it has nothing left to lose by going to war with the state.', '该公司似乎已经得出结论，它在佛蒙特州的声誉已经受到严重损害，它已经没有什么可失去的与州战争。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5551, '2012考研英语一', 'But there should be consequences.', '但应该有后果。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5552, '2012考研英语一', 'Permission to run a nuclear plant is a public trust.', '经营核电站的许可是公众的信任。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5553, '2012考研英语一', 'Entergy runs 11 other reactors in the United States, including Pilgrim Nuclear station in Plymouth.', 'SunGy在美国运行了11个其他反应堆，包括普利茅斯的朝圣核电站。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5554, '2012考研英语一', 'The phrase \"reneging on\" (Line 3.', '“背叛”一词（第3行）。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5555, '2012考研英语一', 'But in the everyday practice of science, discovery frequently follows an ambiguous and complicated route.', '但在科学的日常实践中，发现往往遵循一条模糊而复杂的路径。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5556, '2012考研英语一', 'We aim to be objective, but we cannot escape the context of our unique life experiences.', '我们的目标是客观的，但我们不能逃避我们独特的生活经历的背景。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5557, '2012考研英语一', 'Prior knowledge and interests influence what we experience, what we think our experiences mean, and the subsequent actions we take.', '先前的知识和兴趣影响着我们的经历，我们认为我们的经历意味着什么，以及随后采取的行动。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5558, '2012考研英语一', 'Consequently, discovery claims should be thought of as protoscience.', '因此，发现主张应该被认为是原始科学。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5559, '2012考研英语一', 'Similar to newly staked mining claims, they are full of potential.', '类似于新的采矿索赔，它们充满潜力。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5560, '2012考研英语一', 'But it takes collective scrutiny and acceptance to transform a discovery claim into a mature discovery.', '但它需要集体的审查和接受，将发现的发现转化为成熟的发现。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5561, '2012考研英语一', 'Objective knowledge is the goal, not the starting point.', '客观知识是目标，不是起点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5562, '2012考研英语一', 'Once a discovery claim becomes public, the discoverer receives intellectual credit.', '一旦发现发现成为公开的，发现者就获得了知识信用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5563, '2012考研英语一', 'But, unlike with mining claims, the community takes control of what happens next.', '但是，与采矿索赔不同，社区控制下一步会发生什么。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5564, '2012考研英语一', 'Two paradoxes exist throughout this credibility process.', '在这一可信性的过程中存在着两个悖论。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5565, '2012考研英语一', 'First, scientific work tends to focus on some aspect of prevailing knowledge that is viewed as incomplete or incorrect.', '首先，科学工作往往集中在某些方面的知识，被认为是不完整或不正确的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5566, '2012考研英语一', 'Little reward accompanies duplication and confirmation of what is already known and believed.', '很少的回报伴随着复制和确认已经知道和相信的东西。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5567, '2012考研英语一', 'Not surprisingly, newly published discovery claims and credible discoveries that appear to be important and convincing will always be open to challenge and potential modification or refutation by future researchers.', '毫不奇怪，新近公布的发现声明和可信的发现似乎很重要，而且具有说服力，它们将总是对未来研究人员提出的挑战和潜在的修改或反驳持开放态度。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5568, '2012考研英语一', 'Second, novelty itself frequently provokes disbelief.', '其次，新奇本身经常引起怀疑。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5569, '2012考研英语一', '\" But thinking what nobody else has thought and telling others what they have missed may not change their views.', '但是思考别人没有想到的，告诉别人他们错过了什么，也许不会改变他们的观点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5570, '2012考研英语一', 'Sometimes years are required for truly novel discovery claims to be accepted and appreciated.', '有时候，真正的新发现要求被接受和欣赏需要几年的时间。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5571, '2012考研英语一', 'Which of the following would be the best title of the text.', '下面哪一个是最好的题目？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5572, '2012考研英语一', 'First, they can shut things down without suffering much in the wayof consequences.', '首先，他们可以在不受后果影响的情况下关闭事情。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5573, '2012考研英语一', 'At the state level their influence can be even more fearsome.', '在国家层面上，他们的影响甚至更可怕。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5574, '2012考研英语一', 'In many rich countries average wages in the state sector are higher than in the private one.', '在许多富裕国家，政府部门的平均工资高于私人部门的工资。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5575, '2012考研英语一', 'But the real gains come in benefits and work practices.', '但真正的收获来自于福利和工作实践。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5576, '2012考研英语一', 'As the cost to everyone else has become clearer, politicians have begun to clamp down.', '随着对其他人的成本越来越清楚，政客们开始压制。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5577, '2012考研英语一', 'In Wisconsin the unions have rallied thousands of supporters against Scott Walker, the hardline Republican governor.', '在威斯康星，工会召集了成千上万的支持者反对强硬的共和党州长斯科特·沃克。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5578, '2012考研英语一', 'But many within the public sector suffer under the current system, too.', '但是，公共部门内部的许多人也受到现行体制的影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5579, '2012考研英语一', 'Which of the following is true of Paragraph 2.', '关于第2款，下列哪一项是正确的？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5580, '2012考研英语一', 'There are two extra choices, which do not fit in any of the blanks.', '有两个额外的选择，不适合任何空白。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5581, '2012考研英语一', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEET 1.', '马克在答题纸1上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5582, '2012考研英语一', 'Take a moment or two to wonder at those marvels.', '花一两分钟去琢磨那些奇迹。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5583, '2012考研英语一', 'You are the lucky inheritor of a dream come true.', '你是梦想成真的幸运继承人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5584, '2012考研英语一', 'The networked computer is an amazing device, the first media machine that serves as the mode of production, means of distribution, site of reception, and place of praise and critique.', '网络计算机是一种神奇的设备，它是第一台媒体机器，它充当生产方式、分发手段、接收地点和赞美与批评的地方。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5585, '2012考研英语一', 'But for all the reasons there are to celebrate the computer, we must also act with caution.', '但出于庆祝计算机的原因，我们也必须谨慎行事。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5586, '2012考研英语一', 'I call it a secret war for two reasons.', '我称之为秘密战争有两个原因。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5587, '2012考研英语一', 'First, most people do not realise that there are strong commercial agendas at work to keep them in passive consumption mode.', '首先，大多数人没有意识到工作中存在着强有力的商业议程，以使他们处于被动消费模式。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5588, '2012考研英语一', 'Second, the majority of people who use networked computers to upload are not even aware of the significance of what they are doing.', '其次，大多数使用网络计算机进行上传的人甚至没有意识到他们正在做的事情的重要性。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5589, '2012考研英语一', 'All animals download, but only a few upload.', '所有的动物下载，但只有少数上传。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5590, '2012考研英语一', 'Beavers build dams and birds make nests.', '海狸筑坝，鸟筑巢。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5591, '2012考研英语一', 'Yet for the most part, the animal kingdom moves through the world downloading.', '然而，在大多数情况下，动物王国通过世界下载。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5592, '2012考研英语一', 'Humans are unique in their capacity to not only make tools but then turn around and use them to create superfluous material goods— paintings, sculpture and architecture — and superfluous experiences —music, literature, religion and philosophy.', '人类的独特之处在于，他们不仅能够制造工具，而且能够转过身来使用它们来创造多余的物质物品——绘画、雕塑和建筑——以及多余的体验——音乐、文学、宗教和哲学。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5593, '2012考研英语一', 'For all the possibilities of our new culture machines, most people are still stuck in download mode.', '对于我们的新文化机器的所有可能性，大多数人仍然停留在下载模式。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5594, '2012考研英语一', 'Even after the advent of widespread social media, a pyramid of production remains, with a small number of people uploading material, a slightly larger group commenting on or modifying that content, and a huge percentage remaining content to just consume.', '即使在广泛的社会化媒体出现之后，生产金字塔仍然存在，只有少数人上传材料，稍大一些的群体评论或修改该内容，还有很大一部分剩余内容仅供消费。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5595, '2012考研英语一', 'The hardest task that television asks of anyone is to turn the power off after he has turned it on.', '电视对任何人要求的最艰巨的任务是在他打开电源后关掉电源。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5596, '2012考研英语一', 'What counts as meaningful uploading.', '什么是有意义的上传。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5597, '2012考研英语一', 'My definition revolves around the concept of \"stickiness\" — creations and experiences to which others adhere.', '我的定义围绕着“粘性”的概念——其他人所坚持的创造和体验。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5598, '2012考研英语一', 'Downloading and consuming culture requires great skills, but failing to move beyond downloading is to strip oneself of a defining constituent of humanity.', '下载和消费文化需要高超的技能，但无法超越下载就是剥夺了自己的人性定义。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5599, '2012考研英语一', 'com, which allow users to combine pictures, words and other media in creative ways and then share them, have the potential to add stickiness by amusing, entertaining and enlightening others.', 'com允许用户以创造性的方式将图片、文字和其他媒体结合起来，然后共享它们，它有潜力通过娱乐、娱乐和启发他人来增加粘性。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5600, '2012考研英语一', 'Part C Directions: Read the following text carefully and then translate the underlined segments into Chinese.', 'C部分：仔细阅读下面的文字，然后将下划线段翻译成中文。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5601, '2012考研英语一', 'Your translation should be written clearlyon ANSWER SHEET 2.', '你的翻译应该清楚地写在答题纸2上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5602, '2012考研英语一', 'In some ways, this quest for commonalities defines science.', '在某些方面，对共性的追求定义了科学。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5603, '2012考研英语一', '(46) In physics, one approach takes this impulse for unification to its extreme, and seeks a theory of everything — a single generative equation for all we see.', '（46）在物理学中，一种方法把这种统一的冲动发挥到极致，并寻求万物的理论——一个我们所看到的万物的生成方程。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5604, '2012考研英语一', 'It is becoming less clear, however, that such a theory would be a simplification, given the dimensions and universes that it might entail.', '然而，鉴于这种理论可能涉及的维度和宇宙，这种理论会是一种简化，这一点变得越来越不明确。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5605, '2012考研英语一', 'Nonetheless, unification of sorts remains a major goal.', '尽管如此，统一分类仍然是一个主要目标。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5606, '2012考研英语一', 'This tendency in the natural sciences has long been evident in the social sciences too.', '自然科学的这种趋势在社会科学中也早已显露出来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5607, '2012考研英语一', '(47) Here, Darwinism seems to offer justification, for if all humans share common origins, it seems reasonable to suppose that cultural diversity could also be traced to more constrained beginnings.', '（47）在这里，达尔文主义似乎提供了理由，因为如果所有人类都具有共同的起源，那么认为文化多样性也可追溯到更受限制的起源，这似乎是合理的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5608, '2012考研英语一', '(48)To filter out what is unique from what is shared might enable us to understand how complex cultural behavior arose and what guides it in evolutionary or cognitive terms.', '(48)从共享的事物中过滤出独特的东西，可能使我们能够理解复杂的文化行为是如何产生的，以及从进化或认知的角度指导文化行为的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5609, '2012考研英语一', 'But a comparative study of linguistic traits published online today supplies a reality check.', '但是今天在网上发表的语言特征的对比研究提供了现实的检验。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5610, '2012考研英语一', 'Russell Gray at the University of Auckland and his colleagues consider the evolution of grammars in the light of two previous attempts to find universality in language.', '奥克兰大学的拉塞尔·格雷和他的同事们根据之前两次试图发现语言普遍性的尝试来考虑语法的演变。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5611, '2012考研英语一', 'The most famous of these efforts was initiated by Noam Chomsky, who suggested that humans are born with an innate language—acquisition capacity that dictates a universal grammar.', '这些努力中最著名的是诺姆·乔姆斯基（Noam Chomsky）提出的，他认为人类天生具有决定通用语法的语言习得能力。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5612, '2012考研英语一', 'A few generative rules are then sufficient to unfold the entire fundamental structure of a language, which is why children can learn it so quickly.', '那么一些生成规则就足以展现语言的整个基本结构，这就是为什么孩子们可以如此迅速地学习它。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5613, '2012考研英语一', 'Directions: Section III Writing Some international students are coming to your university.', '方向：第三部分写一些国际学生来到你的大学。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5614, '2012考研英语一', 'Do not sign your own name at the end of the letter.', '不要在信的末尾签上自己的名字。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5615, '2012考研英语一', 'Use \"Li Ming\" instead.', '用“李明”代替。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5616, '2012考研英语一', 'Do not write the address.', '不要写地址。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5617, '2012考研英语一', 'In your essay, you should 1) describe the drawing briefly, 2) explain its intended meaning, and 3) give your comments.', '在你的文章中，你应该1）简单地描述这幅画，2）解释它的意图，3）给出你的评论。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5618, '2012考研英语一', 'You should write neatly on ANSWER SHEET 2.', '你应该整洁地写在答题纸2上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5619, '2012考研英语一', 'But in her new book Join the Club, Tina Rosenberg contends that peer pressure can also be a positive force through what she calls thesocial cure, in which organizations and officials use the power of group dynamics to help individuals improve their lives ', '但是在她的新书《加入俱乐部》中，蒂娜·罗森博格主张，通过她所说的社会治疗，同龄人的压力也可以成为一种积极的力量，在这种社会治疗中，组织和官员利用群体动力学的力量来帮助个人改善他们的生活。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5620, '2012考研英语一', 'The company, a major energy supplier in New England, provoked justified outrage in Vermont last week when it announced it wasreneging on a longstanding commitment to abide by the strict nuclear regulations.', '这家新英格兰的主要能源供应商上周在佛蒙特州宣布，它违背了遵守严格核法规的长期承诺，这激起了人们义愤填膺。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5621, '2012考研英语一', 'The company seems to have concluded that its reputation in Vermont is already so damaged that it has nothing left to lose by going to war with the state.', '该公司似乎已经得出结论，它在佛蒙特州的声誉已经受到严重损害，它已经没有什么可失去的与州战争。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5622, '2012考研英语一', 'Not surprisingly, newly published discovery claims and credible discoveries that appear to be important and convincing will always be open to challenge and potential modification or refutation by future researchers.', '毫不奇怪，新近公布的发现声明和可信的发现似乎很重要，而且具有说服力，它们将总是对未来研究人员提出的挑战和潜在的修改或反驳持开放态度。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5623, '2012考研英语一', '47) Here, Darwinism seems to offer justification, for if all humansshare common origins, it seems reasonable to suppose thatcultural diversity could also be traced to more constrained beginnings.', '47)在这里，达尔文主义似乎提供了理由，因为如果所有的人类都具有共同的起源，那么假设文化多样性也可以追溯到更受限制的起源，这似乎是合理的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5624, '2012考研英语一', '48) To filter out what is unique from what is shared might enableus to understand how complex cultural behavior arose and whatguides it in evolutionary or cognitive terms.', '48)从共享的事物中过滤出独特的事物，可能使我们能够理解复杂的文化行为是如何产生的，以及从进化或认知的角度指导文化行为的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5625, '2012考研英语一', '49) The second, by Joshua Greenberg, takes a more empirical approach to universality, identifying traits (particularly in word order) shared by many languages, which are considered to represent biases that result from cognitive constraints.', '第二，Joshua Greenberg对普遍性采取了更经验性的方法，识别出许多语言所共有的特征（尤其是词序），这些特征被认为是由认知限制导致的偏见。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5626, '2012考研英语一', 'The following suggestions are of great reference to you prior to your coming here.', '以下建议对您在来这里之前有很大的参考价值。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5627, '2012考研英语一', 'First and foremost, it is advisable for you to study Chinese, which will be beneficial to your daily communication, asquickly as possible.', '首先，建议你尽快学习中文，这将有利于你的日常交流。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5628, '2012考研英语一', 'I hope you will find the advice useful.', '我希望你会觉得这些建议有用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5629, '2012考研英语一', 'I hope you will find these proposals useful.', '我希望你会发现这些建议是有用的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5630, '2012考研英语一', 'One man, looking rather upset, says \"There is nothing left.', '一个看起来很沮丧的人说：“什么都没留下。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5631, '2012考研英语一', 'Without any doubt, the purpose of the cartoon is to show us that we should keep optimistic no matter what circumstances we undergo.', '毫无疑问，这幅漫画的目的就是要告诉我们，无论遇到什么情况，我们都应该保持乐观。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5632, '2012考研英语一', 'First and foremost, it is universally held that life is by no means perfect and in the course of life we are bound to experience and encounter a variety of difficulties.', '首先，人们普遍认为，人生绝非完美无缺的，在人生的过程中，我们必然会经历并遇到各种各样的困难。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5633, '2012考研英语一', 'In the second place, according to some research findings, a positive attitude does good to our life in that it will assist us in solving the tough issues.', '其次，根据一些研究发现，积极的态度对我们的生活有好处，因为它可以帮助我们解决棘手的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5634, '2012考研英语一', 'From what has been argued above, we may reasonably arrive at the conclusion that we should embrace positive attitudes and behave confidently.', '根据上面的论点，我们可以合理地得出结论，我们应该接受积极的态度，并且表现得自信。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5635, '2012考研英语一', 'Only in this way can we solve the issues confronting us successfully.', '只有这样，我们才能成功地解决我们面临的问题。');
