INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5651, '2012考研英语二', 'School districts across the country, most recently Los Angeles Unified, are revising their thinking on his educational ritual.', '全国各地的学区，最近洛杉矶统一，正在修改他们的教育仪式的想法。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5652, '2012考研英语二', 'This rule is meant to address the difficulty that students from impoverished or chaotic homes might have in completing their homework.', '这条规定旨在解决来自贫困或混乱家庭的学生在完成家庭作业时可能遇到的困难。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5653, '2012考研英语二', 'But the policy is unclear and contradictory.', '但政策尚不明确，矛盾重重。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5654, '2012考研英语二', 'Certainly, no homework should be assigned that students cannot do without expensive equipment.', '当然，没有作业应该被分配，学生不能没有昂贵的设备。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5655, '2012考研英语二', 'But if the district is essentially giving a pass to students who do not do their homework because of complicated family lives, it is going riskily close to the implication that standards need to be lowered for poor children.', '但如果这个地区基本上是给那些因为复杂的家庭生活而不做作业的学生开一张通行证，那么这就危险地接近了需要降低贫困儿童的标准的暗示。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5656, '2012考研英语二', 'District administrators say that homework will still be a pat of schooling: teachers are allowed to assign as much of it as they want.', '地区行政官员说，家庭作业仍将是学校教育的一部分：教师可以任意分配作业。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5657, '2012考研英语二', 'Some students might do well on state tests without completing their homework, but what about the students who performed well on the tests and did their homework.', '有些学生在没有完成家庭作业的情况下可能考得很好，但是那些在考试中考得很好并完成家庭作业的学生呢？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5658, '2012考研英语二', 'It is quite possible that the homework helped.', '作业很可能是有帮助的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5659, '2012考研英语二', 'At the same time, the policy addresses none of the truly thorny questions about homework.', '同时，该政策没有解决任何关于家庭作业的棘手问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5660, '2012考研英语二', 'Conversely, if homework does nothing to ensure that the homework students are not assigning more than they are willing to review and correct.', '相反，如果家庭作业不能保证学生没有分配更多的作业，他们就会愿意复习和纠正。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5661, '2012考研英语二', 'The homework rules should be put on hold while the school board, which is responsible for setting educational policy, looks into the matter and conducts public hearings.', '当负责制定教育政策的校董会调查此事并举行公开听证会时，家庭作业规则应该被搁置。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5662, '2012考研英语二', 'It is not too late for L.', '对我来说还不算太晚。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5663, '2012考研英语二', 'Unified to do homework right.', '统一做好作业。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5664, '2012考研英语二', 'Girls\' attraction to pink may seem unavoidable, somehow encoded in their DNA, but according to Jo Paoletti, an associate professor of American Studies, it\'s not.', '女孩子对粉红色的吸引力似乎是不可避免的，不知何故，她们的DNA编码着粉红色，但据美国研究学院副教授乔·帕莱蒂（Jo Paoletti）说，事实并非如此。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5665, '2012考研英语二', 'When nursery colours were introduced, pink was actually considered the more masculine colour, a pastel version of red, which was associated with strength.', '当引入苗圃颜色时，粉色实际上被认为是更男性化的颜色，一种柔和的红色，与强度有关。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5666, '2012考研英语二', 'Blue, with its intimations of the Virgin Mary, constancy and faithfulness, symbolised femininity.', '蓝色，带着对Virgin Mary的执着、坚贞和忠诚，象征着女性气质。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5667, '2012考研英语二', 'I had not realised how profoundly marketing trends dictated our perception of what is natural to kids, including our core beliefs about their psychological development.', '我还没有意识到，市场营销趋势深刻地影响着我们对孩子天生的认知，包括我们关于他们心理发展的核心信念。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5668, '2012考研英语二', 'I assumed that phase was something experts developed after years of research into children\'s behaviour: wrong.', '我认为这一阶段是经过多年对儿童行为研究的专家发展出来的：错误的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5669, '2012考研英语二', 'Trade publications counseled department stores that, in order to increase sales, they should create a \"third stepping stone\" between infant wear and older kids\' clothes.', '贸易出版物为百货公司提供咨询，为了增加销售额，他们应该在婴儿服装和年长的儿童服装之间建立一个“第三个踏脚石”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5670, '2012考研英语二', 'It was only after \"toddler\" became common shoppers\' term that it evolved into a broadly accepted developmental stage.', '只有在“蹒跚学步的孩子”成为普通购物者之后，它才演变成一个被广泛接受的发展阶段。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5671, '2012考研英语二', 'According to Paragraph 2, which of the following is true of colours.', '根据第2段，下列哪一项对颜色是正确的？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5672, '2012考研英语二', 'A Colors are encoded in girls\' DNA B Blue used to be regarded as the color for girls C Pink used to be a neutral color in symbolizing genders D White is preferred by babies 28.', '一种颜色编码在女孩的DNA B中，蓝色过去被认为是女孩子的颜色，C粉色过去是中性色，象征着性别D，白色是婴儿28的首选。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5673, '2012考研英语二', 'a federal judge shook America\'s biotech industry to its core.', '一位联邦法官震动了美国的生物技术产业。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5674, '2012考研英语二', 'Executives were violently agitated.', '经理们激动万分。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5675, '2012考研英语二', 'The Biotechnology Industry Organisation (BIO), a trade group, assured members that this was just a \"preliminary step\" in a longer battle.', '生物技术产业组织（BIO），一个贸易组织，向成员们保证，这只是一场较长战役的“初步步骤”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5676, '2012考研英语二', 'On July 29th they were relieved, at least temporarily.', '7月29日，他们得到了缓解，至少是暂时的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5677, '2012考研英语二', 'A federal appeals court overturned the prior decision, ruling that Myriad Genetics could indeed hold patents to two genes that help forecast a woman\'s risk of breast cancer.', '联邦上诉法院推翻了先前的裁决，裁定Myriad Genetics公司确实可以拥有两个有助于预测女性患乳腺癌风险的基因的专利。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5678, '2012考研英语二', 'The chief executive of Myriad, a company in Utah, said the ruling was a blessing to firms and patients alike.', '犹他一家公司的Myrad首席执行官说，这项裁决对公司和病人都是一种祝福。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5679, '2012考研英语二', 'But as companies continue their attempts at personalised medicine, the courts will remain rather busy.', '但随着公司继续尝试个性化医疗，法院将仍然相当繁忙。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5680, '2012考研英语二', 'The Myriad case itself is probably not over.', '无数案件本身可能还没有结束。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5681, '2012考研英语二', 'A growing number seem to agree.', '越来越多的人似乎同意这个观点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5682, '2012考研英语二', 'In October the Department of Justice filed a brief in the Myriad case, arguing that an isolated DNA molecule \"is no less a product of nature.', '10月份，司法部提交了一份关于无数案件的简报，声称一个分离的DNA分子“同样是自然产物”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5683, '2012考研英语二', '\" Despite the appeals court\'s decision, big questions remain unanswered.', '尽管上诉法院做出了决定，但仍有许多问题没有得到解决。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5684, '2012考研英语二', 'For example, it is unclear whether the sequencing of a whole genome violates the patents of individual genes within it.', '例如，目前还不清楚整个基因组的测序是否违背了个体基因的专利。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5685, '2012考研英语二', 'The case may yet reach the Supreme Court.', '此案可能尚未进入最高法院。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5686, '2012考研英语二', 'AS the industry advances, however, other suits may have an even greater impact.', '然而，随着行业的发展，其他西装可能会产生更大的影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5687, '2012考研英语二', 'Their success may be determined by a suit related to this issue, brought by the Mayo Clinic, which the Supreme Court will hear in its next term.', '他们的成功可能取决于梅奥诊所提出的与这个问题有关的诉讼，最高法院将在下学期审理。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5688, '2012考研英语二', 'The BIO recently held a convention which included sessions to coach lawyers on the shifting landscape for patents.', 'BIO最近召开了一个会议，其中包括指导律师们改变专利的景观。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5689, '2012考研英语二', 'Each meeting was packed.', '每次会议都挤满了人。');
