INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5704, '2012考研英语二', 'Before it ends, It will likely change the life course and character of a generation of young adults.', '在它结束之前，它可能会改变一代年轻人的生活历程和性格。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5705, '2012考研英语二', 'And ultimately, it is likely to reshape our politics, our culture, and the character of our society for years.', '最终，它有可能重塑我们的政治、我们的文化和我们社会的性格多年。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5706, '2012考研英语二', 'No one tries harder than the jobless to find silver linings in this national economic disaster.', '在这个国家的经济灾难中，没有人比失业者更努力寻找银线。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5707, '2012考研英语二', 'In limited respects, perhaps the recession will leave society better off.', '在有限的方面，也许经济衰退会让社会变得更好。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5708, '2012考研英语二', 'At the very least, it has awoken us from our national fever dream of easy riches and bigger houses, and put a necessary end to an era of reckless personal spending.', '至少，它唤醒了我们对小康和豪宅的狂热梦想，并且结束了一个鲁莽的个人消费的时代。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5709, '2012考研英语二', 'But for the most part, these benefits seem thin, uncertain, and far off.', '但在大多数情况下，这些好处似乎很薄，不确定，而且很遥远。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5710, '2012考研英语二', 'In The Moral Consequences of Economic Growth, the economic historian Benjamin Friedman argues that both inside and outside the U.', '在经济增长的道德后果中，经济史学家Benjamin Friedman认为美国内外都是如此。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5711, '2012考研英语二', 'Income inequality usually falls during a recession, but it has not shrunk in this one.', '在经济衰退期间，收入不平等通常会下降，但在这一点上没有缩小。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5712, '2012考研英语二', 'In the internet age, it is particularly easy to see the resentment that has always been hidden within American society.', '在互联网时代，特别容易看到的是，在美国社会中一直隐藏着的怨恨。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5713, '2012考研英语二', 'In many respects, the U.', '在很多方面，美国。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5714, '2012考研英语二', 'was more socially tolerant entering this recession than at any time in its history, and a variety of national polls on social conflict since then have shown mixed results.', '进入这次衰退的社会包容性比历史上任何时候都强，自那时以来，关于社会冲突的各种全国民意测验结果喜忧参半。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5715, '2012考研英语二', 'We will have to wait and see exactly how these hard times will reshape our social fabric.', '我们将不得不拭目以待，看看这些艰难时期如何重塑我们的社会结构。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5716, '2012考研英语二', 'But they certainly it, and all the more so the longer they extend.', '但他们确实如此，而且他们延长的时间越长。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5717, '2012考研英语二', 'There are two extra choices in the right column.', '右栏有两个额外的选择。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5718, '2012考研英语二', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEERT 1.', '马克你回答的答案是1。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5719, '2012考研英语二', 'Well, not any more it is not.', '嗯，不再是了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5720, '2012考研英语二', 'Suddenly, Britain looks to have fallen out with its favourite historical form.', '突然间，英国似乎以其最喜欢的历史形式退出了舞台。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5721, '2012考研英语二', 'This could be no more than a passing literary craze, but it also points to a broader truth about how we now approach the past: less concerned with learning from forefathers and more interested in feeling their pain.', '这或许只是一个短暂的文学热潮，但它也指向了一个关于我们现在如何对待过去的更广泛的真理：更少关注向祖先学习，而更多地关注感受他们的痛苦。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5722, '2012考研英语二', 'Today, we want empathy, not inspiration.', '今天，我们需要的是同情，而不是灵感。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5723, '2012考研英语二', 'From the earliest days of the Renaissance, the writing of history meant recounting the exemplary lives of great men.', '从文艺复兴的早期开始，历史的书写就意味着讲述伟人的模范生活。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5724, '2012考研英语二', 'Petrarch celebrated their greatness in conquering fortune and rising to the top.', '彼得拉奇在征服财富和登上顶峰时庆祝他们的伟大。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5725, '2012考研英语二', 'This was the biographical tradition which Niccolo Machiavelli turned on its head.', '这是传记的传统，Niccolo Machiavelli转过身来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5726, '2012考研英语二', 'In The Prince, the championed cunning, ruthlessness, and boldness, rather than virtue, mercy and justice, as the skills of successful leaders.', '在《王子》中，拥护者狡猾、无情、勇敢，而不是美德、仁慈和正义，作为成功领导者的技能。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5727, '2012考研英语二', 'Over time, the attributes of greatness shifted.', '随着时间的推移，伟大的属性发生了转变。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5728, '2012考研英语二', 'The Romantics commemorated the leading painters and authors of their day, stressing the uniqueness of the artist\'s personal experience rather than public glory.', '浪漫主义者纪念他们那个时代的主要画家和作家，强调艺术家个人经历的独特性，而不是公众的荣耀。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5729, '2012考研英语二', '\"what it is in the power of each to accomplish for himself.', '“每个人的力量是如何为自己完成的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5730, '2012考研英语二', '\" His biographies of James Walt, Richard Arkwright and Josiah Wedgwood were held up as beacons to guide the working man through his difficult life.', '他关于詹姆斯·沃尔特、理查德·阿克赖特和乔西亚·韦奇伍德的传记被当作指引这位工人度过艰难生活的灯塔。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5731, '2012考研英语二', 'This was all a bit bourgeois for Thomas Carlyle, who focused his biographies on the truly heroic lives of Martin Luther, Oliver Cromwell and Napoleon Bonaparte.', '这对托马斯·卡莱尔来说都是些中产阶级的东西，他的传记主要描写了马丁·路德、奥利弗·克伦威尔和拿破仑·波拿巴的真实英雄生活。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5732, '2012考研英语二', 'These epochal figures represented lives hard to imitate, but to be acknowledged as possessing higher authority than mere mortals.', '这些时代人物代表着难以模仿的生活，但被公认为拥有比凡人更高的权威。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5733, '2012考研英语二', 'For them, history did nothing, it possessed no immense wealth nor waged battles: \"It is man, real, living man who does all that.', '对他们来说，历史并没有什么，它没有巨大的财富，也没有激烈的战斗：“是人类，真实的，活着的人，他们做了所有这些事情。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5734, '2012考研英语二', '\" And history should be the story of the masses and their record of struggle.', '“历史应该是群众的故事和斗争的记录。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5735, '2012考研英语二', 'As such, it needed to appreciate the economic realities, the social contexts and power relations in which each epoch stood.', '因此，它需要了解每个时代所处的经济现实、社会背景和权力关系。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5736, '2012考研英语二', '\" This was the tradition which revolutionized our appreciation of the past.', '“这是一个传统，它改变了我们对过去的欣赏。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5737, '2012考研英语二', 'In place of Thomas Carlyle, Britain nurtured Christopher Hill, EP Thompson and Eric Hobsbawm.', '代替托马斯·卡莱尔，英国培养了Christopher Hill、EP汤普森和霍布斯邦。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5738, '2012考研英语二', 'History from below stood alongside biographies of great men.', '下面的历史站在伟人传记的旁边。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5739, '2012考研英语二', 'And it transformed public history too: downstairs became just as fascinating as upstairs.', '它也改变了公共历史：楼下变得跟楼上一样迷人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5740, '2012考研英语二', 'Part C Directions: Read the following text carefully and then translate it into Chinese.', 'C部分：仔细阅读下面的文字，然后翻译成中文。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5741, '2012考研英语二', 'Your translation should be written clearly on ANSWER SHEET 2.', '你的翻译应该清楚地写在答题纸2上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5742, '2012考研英语二', '( 15 points) When people in developing countries worry about migration, they are usually concerned at the prospect of their best and brightest departure to Silicon Valsey or to hospitals and universities in the developed world.', '(15)当发展中国家的人们担心移民问题时，他们通常担心他们最好和最光明的出发地去硅谷或去发达国家的医院和大学的前景。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5743, '2012考研英语二', 'These are the kind of workers that countries like Britain Canada and Australia try to attract by using immigration rules that privilege college graduates.', '这些是像英国、加拿大和澳大利亚这样的国家试图通过利用移民规定来吸引大学毕业生的那种工人。');
