INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5845, '2013考研英语一', 'One of these urges has to do with creating a state of peace in the midst of turbulence, a \"still point of the turning world,\" to borrow a phrase from T.', '这些敦促之一是借用T.');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5846, '2013考研英语一', '(47) A sacred place of peace, however crude it may be, is a distinctly human need, as opposed to shelter, which is a distinctly animal need.', '（47）一个神圣的和平场所，无论它多么粗鲁，都是人类的明显需要，而庇护所则是动物的明显需要。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5847, '2013考研英语一', 'This distinction is so much so that where the latter is lacking, as it is for these unlikely gardens, the former becomes all the more urgent.', '这种区别是如此之大，以至于在缺乏后者的地方，正如这些不太可能的花园一样，前者变得更加紧迫。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5848, '2013考研英语一', 'In so doing they give composure to a segment of the inarticulate environment in which they take their stand.', '在这样做的过程中，他们对一部分无法言说的环境给予了镇静。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5849, '2013考研英语一', 'Another urge or need that these gardens appear to respond to, or to arise from, is so intrinsic that we are barely ever conscious of its abiding claims on us.', '这些花园似乎回应或产生的另一个冲动或需求是如此内在，以至于我们几乎从未意识到它对我们的持久要求。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5850, '2013考研英语一', 'When we are deprived of green, of plants, of trees, (49) most of us give in to a demoralization of spirit which weusually blame on some psychological conditions, until one day we find ourselves in a garden and feel the oppression vanish as if by magic.', '当我们被剥夺了绿色、植物和树木，（49）我们中的大多数人屈服于精神的堕落，这种堕落通常归咎于一些心理状况，直到有一天我们发现自己在花园里，感觉压迫就像被魔法消灭了一样。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5851, '2013考研英语一', 'In most of the homeless gardens of New York City the actual cultivation of plants is unfeasible, yet even so the compositions often seem to represent attempts to call forth the spirit of plant and animal life, if only symbolically, through a clumplike arr', '在纽约市大多数无家可归的花园中，实际种植植物是不可行的，但即使如此，这些作品似乎也常常象征着试图通过象徵性的箭头，唤起植物和动物生命的精神。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5852, '2013考研英语一', 'On display here are various fantasy elements whose reference, at some basic level, seems to be the natural world.', '这里展示的是各种幻想元素，它们在某些基本层面上似乎是自然世界的参照物。');
