INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5950, '2013考研英语二', 'There are concerns that government, employers, and marketers might be able to access these data, thereby violating our privacy.', '人们担心政府、雇主和营销人员可能会访问这些数据，从而侵犯了我们的隐私权。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5951, '2013考研英语二', 'Given the advantages of electronic money,you might think that we would move quickly to the cashless society in which all payments are made electronically.', '考虑到电子货币的优势，你可能会认为我们会迅速进入无现金社会，所有支付都是电子化的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5952, '2013考研英语二', 'Third, the use of paper checks gives consumers several days of \"float\"—— it takes several days of the check can earn interest on the funds in the meantime.', '第三，使用纸质支票给消费者几天的“浮动”——它需要几天的支票才能同时赚取资金的利息。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5953, '2013考研英语二', 'Davidson\'s article is one of a number of pieces that have recently appeared making the point that the reason we have such stubbornly high unemployment and declining middleclass incomes today is also because of the advances in both globalization and the in', '戴维森的文章是最近出现的一些文章之一，这些文章指出，我们今天居高不下的失业率和中产阶级收入下降的原因也是由于全球化的进步和国内的进步。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5954, '2013考研英语二', 'Bill for the 21st century that ensures that every American has access to posthigh school education.', '比尔的二十一世纪，确保每一个美国人都有机会接受高等教育。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5955, '2013考研英语二', 'They prefer to come and go as opportunity calls them.', '他们宁愿来来去去，正如机会召唤他们一样。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5956, '2013考研英语二', 'They can manage to have a job in one place and a family in another.', '他们可以在一个地方找到工作，另一个家庭可以工作。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5957, '2013考研英语二', 'Along with the many folks looking to make a permanent home inthe United States came those who had no intention to stay, and 7 million people arrived while about 2 million departed.', '与许多想在美国建立永久家园的人一起，还有那些无意留下来的人，700万人到达，而大约200万人离开了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5958, '2013考研英语二', 'We need them to imagine the United States as a place where they can be productive for a while without committing themselves to staying forever.', '我们需要他们把美国想象成一个地方，在那里他们可以有一段时间的生产力，而不必承诺永远停留。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5959, '2013考研英语二', 'Scientists have found that although we are prone to snap overreactions, if we take a moment and think about how we are likely to react, we can reduce or even eliminate the negative effects of our quick, hardwired responses.', '科学家们发现，尽管我们容易突然反应过度，但如果我们花点时间想想我们可能会如何反应，我们就能减少甚至消除我们快速而有条理的反应的负面影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5960, '2013考研英语二', 'When women do break through to the summit of corporate power—as, for example, Sheryl Sandberg recently did at Facebook—they attract massive attention precisely because they remain the exception to the rule.', '当女性真正突破公司权力之巅时，比如谢丽尔·桑德伯格（Sheryl Sandberg）最近在脸谱网（Facebook）所做的，她们吸引了大量的关注，正是因为她们仍然是这个规则的例外。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5961, '2013考研英语二', 'If appropriate public policies were in place to help all women—whether CEOs or their children\'s caregivers—and all families, Sandberg would be no more newsworthy than any other highly capable person living in a more just society.', '如果制定适当的公共政策来帮助所有妇女——无论是首席执行官还是其子女的看护者——以及所有家庭，桑德伯格就不会比生活在一个更公正社会中的任何其他高度有能力的人更有新闻价值。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5962, '2013考研英语二', 'Soon you\'ll feel comfortable asking if they\'ve any knuckles of ham for soups and stews, or beef bones, chicken carcasses and fish heads for stock which, more often than not, they\'ll let you have for free.', '很快，你会觉得很舒服，问他们是否有汤和炖肉用的火腿节，或者牛肉骨、鸡肉和鱼头做原料，通常他们会免费让你吃。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5963, '2013考研英语二', 'I can recall the day my grandfather died and the sadness I felt when we went to the hospital the day before.', '我记得我祖父去世的那一天，前一天我们去医院时的悲伤。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5964, '2013考研英语二', 'I also remember that the musical play Hair opened on the Broadway on the same day—they both just pop into my mind in the same way.', '我还记得音乐剧《头发》在同一天在百老汇上映，它们都以同样的方式出现在我的脑海里。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (5965, '2013考研英语二', 'Those kids who come from remote areas lack proper and fine education.', '那些来自偏远地区的孩子缺乏适当和良好的教育。');
