INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6500, '2016考研英语一', 'Buy all your clothes at once with a stylist instead of shopping alone, one article of clothing at a time.', '一次买一件衣服而不是一个设计师，一次买一件衣服。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6501, '2016考研英语一', 'Part C Directions: Read the following text carefully and then translate the underlined segments into Chinese.', 'C部分：仔细阅读下面的文字，然后将下划线段翻译成中文。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6502, '2016考研英语一', 'Your translation should be written neatly on the ANSWER SHEET.', '你的翻译应该写在答题纸上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6503, '2016考研英语一', 'It is like immune system of the body, which under stress or through lack of nutrition or exercise can be weakened, but which never leaves us.', '它就像身体的免疫系统，在压力下或通过缺乏营养或运动可以削弱，但它永远不会离开我们。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6504, '2016考研英语一', '(48) Mental health allows us to view others with sympathy if they are having troubles, with kindness if they are in pain, and with unconditional love no matter who they are.', '（48）心理健康允许我们在别人遇到困难时给予同情，在痛苦时给予善意，无论他们是谁，给予无条件的爱。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6505, '2016考研英语一', 'Mental health is the source of creativity for solving problems, resolving conflict, making our surroundings more beautiful, managing our home life, or coming up with a creative business idea or invention to make our lives easier.', '心理健康是解决问题、解决冲突、使我们的环境更美好、管理我们的家庭生活、或者想出一个创造性的商业想法或发明来使我们的生活更容易的创造力的源泉。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6506, '2016考研英语一', 'It gives us patience for ourselves.', '它给我们自己的耐心。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6507, '2016考研英语一', 'And toward others as well as patience while driving, catching a fish, working on our car, or raising a child.', '以及对他人的耐心和驾驶，捕鱼，在车上工作，或抚养孩子。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6508, '2016考研英语一', 'It allows us to see the beauty that surrounds us each moment in nature, in culture, in the flow of our daily lives.', '它让我们看到周围的美，无论是在大自然中，还是在文化中，在日常生活的流动中。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6509, '2016考研英语一', 'It has been available even in the most mundane of life situations to show you right from wrong, good from bad, friend from foe.', '即使在最平凡的生活环境中，它也能显示你是对错、好与坏、朋友与敌人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6510, '2016考研英语一', 'Mental health has commonly been called conscience, instinct, wisdom, common sense, or the inner voice, we think of it simply as a health and helpful flow of intelligent thought.', '心理健康通常被称作良心、本能、智慧、常识或内在的声音，我们认为它仅仅是一种健康的、有益的智能思维流。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6511, '2016考研英语一', 'Directions: Suppose you are a librarian in your university.', '方向：假设你是一个图书馆员在你的大学。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6512, '2016考研英语一', 'You should write neatly on the ANSWER SHEET.', '你应该在答题纸上整洁地写。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6513, '2016考研英语一', 'Do not sign your own name at the end of the notice.', '不要在通知的末尾签上自己的名字。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6514, '2016考研英语一', 'Do not write the address.', '不要写地址。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6515, '2016考研英语一', 'Do not write the address.', '不要写地址。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6516, '2016考研英语一', 'increase it at a higher rate each year.', '每年以更高的速度增加。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6517, '2016考研英语一', 'The university library opens at 8 a.', '大学图书馆8点开馆。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6518, '2016考研英语一', 'from Monday to Friday, but from 9 a.', '从星期一到星期五，但是从9点开始。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6519, '2016考研英语一', 'If you need to borrow books, please follow the following steps.', '如果您需要借阅图书，请按照下列步骤操作。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6520, '2016考研英语一', 'At most six books can be borrowed once from the library.', '最多有六本书可以从图书馆借一次。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6521, '2016考研英语一', 'You should keep in mind the days that you can keep the book(s) you borrow.', '你应该记住借书的日子。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6522, '2016考研英语一', 'Three months is the longest period.', '三个月是最长的时期。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6523, '2016考研英语一', 'If you exceed the limited time, some fines should be paid.', '如果超过限期，应缴纳罚款。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6524, '2016考研英语一', 'We sincerely hope you all enjoy the study and life in our university.', '我们衷心希望你们都能享受到我们大学的学习和生活。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6525, '2016考研英语一', 'In the first picture, the father is urging his son to study hard while he is smoking and watching TV idly.', '在第一张照片中，父亲在鼓励儿子努力学习，一边抽烟一边看电视。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6526, '2016考研英语一', 'In the second picture, the father and his son are both concentrating on the study.', '在第二幅图中，父亲和他的儿子都集中在研究上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6527, '2016考研英语一', 'The caption under the cartoon reads: \"It is better to set an example than to make demands\".', '漫画下面的标题写着：“树立榜样比提出要求更好。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6528, '2016考研英语一', 'Apparently, the author of the cartoon focuses on a fact that many parents when educating their children tend to neglect the impact of their own acts upon their children.', '显然，这幅漫画的作者着重于这样一个事实，即许多父母在教育孩子时往往忽视他们自己的行为对孩子的影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6529, '2016考研英语一', 'It is without any doubt that all parents hope that their children could have a bright future.', '毫无疑问，所有的父母都希望他们的孩子有一个光明的未来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6530, '2016考研英语一', 'Therefore, they tend to count on schools and the society to provide their kids with a good education.', '因此，他们倾向于指望学校和社会为他们的孩子提供良好的教育。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6531, '2016考研英语一', 'Parents failing to set a role model for their children will only result in an unhealthy family atmosphere, which is definitely harmful to the future development of their children.', '父母不给孩子树立榜样，只会导致不健康的家庭氛围，这无疑不利于孩子未来的发展。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6532, '2016考研英语一', 'Therefore, parents should provide their children with a favorable growing environment by being a positive role model.', '因此，父母应通过积极的榜样为孩子提供良好的成长环境。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6533, '2016考研英语一', 'Only through persistent efforts and proper guidance can children enjoy a bright future.', '只有通过不懈的努力和正确的引导，孩子才能有一个光明的未来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6534, '2016考研英语二', 'Companies located in places with happier people invest more, according to a recent research paper.', '根据最近的一份研究报告，位于快乐的地方的公司投资更多。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6535, '2016考研英语二', 'Firms seem to invest more in places where most people are relatively happy, rather than in places with happiness inequality.', '企业似乎更多地投资于大多数人相对快乐的地方，而不是在幸福不平等的地方。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6536, '2016考研英语二', 'Answer the questions after each text by choosing A, B, C or D.', '通过选择A、B、C或D来回答每个文本后的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6537, '2016考研英语二', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEET 1.', '马克在答题纸1上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6538, '2016考研英语二', 'However, Cortina said, early exposure is beneficial.', '不过，Cortina表示，早期接触是有益的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6539, '2016考研英语二', 'Giving more children this training could increase the number of people interested in the field and help fill the jobs gap, Cortina said.', '科蒂娜说，给更多的孩子这种培训可以增加对这一领域感兴趣的人数，并有助于填补工作空缺。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6540, '2016考研英语二', 'For instance, one of the apps the students are developing suggests movies based on your mood.', '例如，学生开发的应用程序之一是根据你的心情建议电影。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6541, '2016考研英语二', 'Programming languages have a quick turnover, so the \"Ruby on Rails\" language they learned may not even be relevant by the time they enter the job market.', '编程语言的转换速度很快，所以他们所学的“Ruby on Rails”语言在进入就业市场时甚至可能并不相关。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6542, '2016考研英语二', 'But the skills they learn — how to think logically through a problem and organize the results — apply to any coding language, said Deborah Seehorn, an education consultant for the state of North Carolina.', '但是北卡罗来纳州的教育顾问Deborah Seehorn说，他们学到的技能——如何通过问题进行逻辑思考并组织结果——适用于任何编码语言。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6543, '2016考研英语二', 'Indeed, the Flatiron students might not go into IT at all.', '事实上，熨斗的学生可能根本不会参与其中。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6544, '2016考研英语二', 'But creating a future army of coders is not the sole purpose of the classes.', '但是创建一个未来的程序员队伍并不是班级的唯一目的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6545, '2016考研英语二', 'These kids are going to be surrounded by computers — in their pockets, in their offices, in their homes — for the rest of their lives.', '这些孩子将终生被电脑包围——在他们的口袋里，在他们的办公室里，在他们的家里。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6546, '2016考研英语二', 'The younger they learn how computers think, how to coax the machine into producing what they want — the earlier they learn that they have the power to do that — the better.', '他们越早学会计算机如何思考，如何哄骗机器生产他们想要的东西——他们越早知道自己有能力这样做——越好。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6547, '2016考研英语二', 'remodel the way of thinking C.', '重塑思维方式C。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6548, '2016考研英语二', 'formulate logical hypotheses D.', '制定逻辑假设D。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6549, '2016考研英语二', 'perfect artwork production 22.', '完美的艺术品生产22。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6550, '2016考研英语二', 'academic backgrounds C.', '学术背景C.');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6551, '2016考研英语二', 'help students learn other computer languages B.', '帮助学生学习其他计算机语言B。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6552, '2016考研英语二', 'have to be upgraded when new technologies come C.', '当新技术出现时必须升级。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6553, '2016考研英语二', 'need improving when students look for jobs D.', '当学生找工作时需要改进。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6554, '2016考研英语二', 'enable students to make big quick money 24.', '让学生赚大钱快24。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6555, '2016考研英语二', 'compete with a future army of programmers B.', '与未来的程序员B竞争。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6556, '2016考研英语二', 'stay longer in the information technology industry C.', '在信息技术行业停留更长时间。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6557, '2016考研英语二', 'become better prepared for the digitalized world D.', '为数字化世界做好准备。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6558, '2016考研英语二', 'bring forth innovative computer technologies 25.', '创新计算机技术25。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6559, '2016考研英语二', 'The word \"coax\" (Line4, Para.', '“同轴电缆”一词（Para）');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6560, '2016考研英语二', 'The crash was a major reason the U.', '这次撞车是U.的主要原因。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6561, '2016考研英语二', 'S Fish and Wildlife Service (USFWS)decided to formally list the bird as threatened.', '美国鱼类和野生动物服务局（UFWS）决定正式将这只鸟列入威胁名单。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6562, '2016考研英语二', '\"The lesser prairie chicken is in a desperate situation,\" said USFWS Director Daniel Ashe.', '“小草原鸡正处于绝望境地，”美国渔农自然护理委员会主任丹尼尔·阿什说。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6563, '2016考研英语二', 'Some environmentalists, however, were disappointed.', '然而，一些环保主义者感到失望。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6564, '2016考研英语二', 'They had pushed the agency to designate the bird as \"endangered,\" a status that gives federal officials greater regulatory power to crack down on threats.', '他们敦促该机构将这只鸟定为“濒危鸟”，这一地位使联邦官员有更大的监管权力来打击威胁。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6565, '2016考研英语二', 'But Ashe and others argued that the \"threatened\" tag gave the federal government flexibility to try out new, potentially less confrontational conservations approaches.', '但阿什和其他人认为，“威胁”标签给联邦政府灵活尝试新的，潜在的较少对抗的保护方法。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6566, '2016考研英语二', 'Under the plan, for example, the agency said it would not prosecute landowner or businesses that unintentionally kill, harm, or disturb the bird, as long as they had signed a range—wide management plan to restore prairie chicken habitat.', '例如，根据该计划，该机构表示，只要他们签署了一个范围广泛的管理计划来恢复草原鸡栖息地，就不会起诉无意杀害、伤害或扰乱鸟的土地所有者或企业。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6567, '2016考研英语二', 'Negotiated by USFWS and the states, the plan requires individuals and businesses that damage habitat as part of their operations to pay into a fund to replace every acre destroyed with 2 new acres of suitable habitat.', '由USFWS和各州协商，该计划要求破坏栖息地的个人和企业作为其业务的一部分，支付一笔资金，以取代每英亩被破坏的2新英亩合适的栖息地。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6568, '2016考研英语二', 'And it gives the Western Association of Fish and Wildlife Agencies (WAFWA), a coalition of state agencies, the job of monitoring progress.', '它还赋予了西部鱼类和野生动物机构协会（WAFWA），一个州政府机构的联盟，监督进展的工作。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6569, '2016考研英语二', 'In fact, \"becoming more efficient\" is part of the problem.', '事实上，“变得更有效率”是问题的一部分。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6570, '2016考研英语二', 'Perhaps surprisingly, scheduling regular times for reading.', '也许令人惊讶的是，安排规律的阅读时间。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6571, '2016考研英语二', 'Across generational lines, Americans continue to prize many of the same traditional milestones of a successful life, including getting married, having children, owning a home, and retiring in their sixties.', '跨越几代人的界限，美国人继续珍视许多成功生活的传统里程碑，包括结婚、生孩子、拥有一个家，以及六十多岁退休。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6572, '2016考研英语二', 'But while young and old mostly agree on what constitutes the finish line of a fulfilling life, they offer strikingly different paths for reaching it.', '但是，尽管年轻人和老年人在什么是充实生活的终点线上基本达成一致，但他们为达到这一目标提供了截然不同的途径。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6573, '2016考研英语二', 'Young people who are still getting started in life were more likely than older adults to prioritize personal fulfillment in their work, to believe they will advance their careers most by regularly changing jobs, to favor communities with more public servi', '仍然处于起步阶段的年轻人比年长者更有可能在工作中优先考虑个人成就感，相信通过定期换工作，他们最能提升自己的职业，更喜欢公共服务较多的社区。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6574, '2016考研英语二', 'From career to community and family, these contrasts suggest that in the aftermath of the searing Great Recession, those just starting out in life are defining priorities and expectations that will increasingly spread through virtually all aspects of Amer', '从职业到社区和家庭，这些对比表明，在剧烈的经济衰退之后，那些刚刚开始生活的人正在确定优先事项和期望，这些优先事项和期望将越来越多地传播到美国的几乎所有方面。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6575, '2016考研英语二', 'Young and old converge on one key point: Overwhelming majorities of both groups said they believe it is harder for young people today to get started in life than it was for earlier generations.', '年轻人和老年人会聚到一个关键点上：两组的绝大多数人表示，他们相信现在的年轻人比前几代人更难开始生活。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6576, '2016考研英语二', 'Pete Schneider considers the climb tougher today.', 'Pete Schneider认为今天的攀登更加艰难。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6577, '2016考研英语二', 'Even now that he is working steadily, he said.', '他说，即使现在他正在稳步地工作。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6578, '2016考研英语二', '\" Looking back, he is struck that his parents could provide a comfortable life for their children even though neither had completed college when he was young.', '回顾过去，他惊讶于他的父母能为他们的孩子提供舒适的生活，即使他年轻时没有完成大学。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6579, '2016考研英语二', 'Which of the following is true about Schneider.', '关于Schneider，下列哪一项是正确的？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6580, '2016考研英语二', 'There are two extra subheadings which you do not need to use.', '有两个额外的子标题，您不需要使用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6581, '2016考研英语二', 'Mark your answers on the ANSWER SHEET.', '马克在答题纸上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6582, '2016考研英语二', 'instead,they look after their wellbeing instinctively,and usually more effectively than we do as grownups.', '相反，他们本能地照顾自己的健康，通常比成年人更有效。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6583, '2016考研英语二', 'Perhaps it\'s time to learn a few lessons from them.', '也许是时候从他们身上学到一些教训了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6584, '2016考研英语二', 'Probably a bit of both.', '可能两者兼而有之。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6585, '2016考研英语二', 'As we grow up,we learn to control our emotions so they are manageable and don\'t dictate our behaviours,which is in many ways a good thing.', '随着我们长大，我们学会控制自己的情绪，这样情绪就能被控制住，而不会左右我们的行为，这在很多方面都是件好事。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6586, '2016考研英语二', 'But too often we take this process too far and end up suppressing emotions,especially negative ones.', '但我们往往太过重视这一过程，最终压制情绪，尤其是消极情绪。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6587, '2016考研英语二', 'that\'s about as effective as brushing dirt under a carpet and can even make us ill.', '这就像刷地毯下的灰尘一样有效，甚至会让我们生病。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6588, '2016考研英语二', 'It cost less than a fiver but she was overjoyed, and couldn\'t stop talking about it.', '它的成本比一个小，但她欣喜若狂，无法停止谈论它。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6589, '2016考研英语二', 'Too often we believe that a new job,bigger house or better car will be the magic silver bullet that will allow us to finally be content,but the reality is these things have very little lasting impact on our happiness levels.', '我们常常相信，一份新工作、更大的房子或更好的汽车会是让我们最终满足的神奇的银弹，但现实是这些东西对我们的幸福水平几乎没有持久的影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6590, '2016考研英语二', 'If we adults could indulge in a bit of silliness and giggling, we would reduce the stress hormones in our bodies , increase good hormones like endorphins, improve blood flow to our hearts and even have a greater chance of fighting off enfection.', '如果我们的成年人能够沉溺于一些愚蠢和咯咯的笑声，我们就能减少体内的压力荷尔蒙，增加像内啡肽这样的好荷尔蒙，改善流向心脏的血流，甚至有更大的机会抵御感染。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6591, '2016考研英语二', 'All of which, of course, have a positive effect on happiness levels.', '当然，所有这些都会对幸福水平产生积极的影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6592, '2016考研英语二', 'But as adults we also have the luxury of being able to control our own diaries and it\'s important that we schedule in time to enjoy the things we love.', '但是作为成年人，我们也有能够控制自己的日记的奢侈，并且及时安排时间去享受我们喜爱的事情是很重要的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6593, '2016考研英语二', 'Those things might be social,sporting,creative or completely random(dancing aroud the living room,anyone.', '这些东西可能是社会的、体育的、创造性的或完全随机的（起舞）起居室，任何人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6594, '2016考研英语二', 'Scientists tell us this can backfire and actually have a negative impact on our wellbeing.', '科学家告诉我们，这会适得其反，实际上会对我们的健康产生负面影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6595, '2016考研英语二', 'As the Chinese philosopher Chuang Tzu is reported to have said:\"Happiness is the absence of striving for happiness.', '据报道，中国哲学家Chuang Tzu曾说过：“幸福是不为幸福而奋斗的。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6596, '2016考研英语二', '\"And in that,once more,we need to look to the example of our children,to whom happiness is not a goal but a natural by product of the way they live.', '“在这一点上，我们再一次需要看看我们孩子的例子，对他们来说，幸福不是目的，而是他们生活方式的自然产物。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6597, '2016考研英语二', 'Section III Translation Directions: Translate the following text from English into Chinese.', '第三部分翻译方向：从英文翻译成中文。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6598, '2016考研英语二', 'Write your translation on ANSWER SHEET 2.', '把你的翻译写在答题纸2上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6599, '2016考研英语二', 'Directions: Translate the following text into Chinese.', '说明：将下列文字翻译成中文。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6600, '2016考研英语二', 'Your translation should be written on the ANSWER SHEET.', '你的翻译应该写在答题纸上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6601, '2016考研英语二', '(15 points) The supermarket is designed to lure customers into spending as much time as possible within its doors.', '（15点）超市旨在吸引顾客尽可能多地在门内消费。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6602, '2016考研英语二', 'The reason for this is simple:The longer you stay in the store, the more stuff you\'ll see, and the more stuff you see, the more you\'ll buy.', '原因很简单：你在商店待的时间越长，你看到的东西就越多，你看到的东西越多，你买的东西就越多。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6603, '2016考研英语二', 'And supermarkets contain a lot of stuff.', '超市里有很多东西。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6604, '2016考研英语二', 'The sheer volume of available choice is enough to send shoppers into a state of information overload.', '可供选择的绝对数量足以让购物者陷入信息过载的状态。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6605, '2016考研英语二', 'Section IV Writing Part A Suppose you won a translation contest and your friend Jack wrote an email to congratulate you, and ask advice on translation.', '假设你赢得了翻译比赛，你的朋友杰克写了一封电子邮件向你表示祝贺，并询问翻译建议。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6606, '2016考研英语二', 'Do not sign you own name at the end of the letter, use \"Li Ming \" instead.', '不要在信的末尾签上自己的名字，而是用“李明”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6607, '2016考研英语二', 'Do not write the address.', '不要写地址。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6608, '2016考研英语二', 'Directions: Write an essay based on the following chart.', '方向：写一篇基于以下图表的文章。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6609, '2016考研英语二', 'you should 1) interpret the chart and 2) give your comments.', '你应该1）解释图表和2）给出你的评论。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6610, '2016考研英语二', 'Thank you for your nice words on my winning the c ontest.', '谢谢你的好话，我赢得了第一次考试。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6611, '2016考研英语二', 'In the letter, you asked me about the skills to do translation, so the following are my a dvice for you.', '在信中，你问我关于翻译的技巧，所以以下是我的一个副手。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6612, '2016考研英语二', 'Firstly, you should analyze the sentence structure, thus catching the meaning of the sentence.', '首先，你应该分析句子结构，从而抓住句子的意思。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6613, '2016考研英语二', 'Secondly, find the proper words to translate the meaning of the source language into the target l anguage.', '其次，找到合适的词语把源语言的意义翻译成目标L语言。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6614, '2016考研英语二', 'Thirdly, revise your translation at least three times to check if there are any mistransl ations or missed meanings.', '第三，修改你的翻译至少三次，检查是否有任何错误或遗漏的意思。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6615, '2016考研英语二', 'I hope my advice helpful.', '我希望我的建议有帮助。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6616, '2016考研英语二', 'Wish to see you soon.', '希望很快见到你。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6617, '2016考研英语二', 'The numb er of students who take traveling as a chance to see beautiful scenes accounts for 37%, while stu dents who would like to travel to relieve pressure from study take up 35 %.', '以旅游为机会看美景的学生中，麻木的学生占37%，而想通过旅游来缓解学习压力的学生占35%。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6618, '2016考研英语二', 'There are several reasons behind the trend revealed in the above chart.', '上述图表揭示了这一趋势背后的几个原因。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6619, '2016考研英语二', 'To begin with, as the pr esent society is filled with fierce competition, most college students nowadays are under great pr essure to stand out among others or to lunch a decent job after graduation.', '首先，当今社会竞争激烈，大多数大学生都面临着脱颖而出或毕业后找份体面的工作的巨大压力。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6620, '2016考研英语二', 'Therefore, they tend to choose traveling as an outlet to relieve their stress.', '因此，他们倾向于选择旅行作为缓解压力的途径。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6621, '2016考研英语二', 'Secondly, with the fast advancement of t he living standards of Chinese families, traveling is increasingly affordable to most college stude nts.', '其次，随着中国家庭生活水平的快速提高，大多数大学生的旅游负担越来越高。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6622, '2016考研英语二', 'For this reason, students prefer to travel to see different views to enjoy themselves or to m ake some friends.', '由于这个原因，学生更喜欢旅行，看到不同的意见，享受自己或一些朋友。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6623, '2017考研英语一', 'Choose the best word (s) for each numbered blank and mark A, B, C or D on the ANSWER SHEET.', '为每个编号的空白选择最佳单词，并在答题纸上标出A、B、C或D。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6624, '2017考研英语一', 'Believe it or not, a warm embrace might even help you 4 getting sick this winter.', '信不信由你，一个温暖的拥抱甚至可以帮助你今年冬天生病4次。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6625, '2017考研英语一', '11 among those who got a cold, the ones who felt greater social support and received more frequent hugs had less severe 12.', '11在感冒患者中，那些感觉到更大社会支持和更频繁拥抱的人没有那么严重的12。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6626, '2017考研英语一', 'Hugging \"is a marker of intimacy and helps 15 the feeling that others are there to help 16 difficulty.', '拥抱是一种亲密的标志，帮助15的人感觉到有助于16的困难。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6627, '2017考研英语一', 'Oxytocin is made primarily in the central lower part of the brain, and some of it is released into the bloodstream.', '催产素主要是在大脑的中央下部，其中一些被释放到血流中。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6628, '2017考研英语一', 'Answer the questions below each text by choosing A, B, C or D.', '通过选择A、B、C或D回答每个文本下面的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6629, '2017考研英语一', 'Mark your answers on the ANSWER SHEET.', '马克在答题纸上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6630, '2017考研英语一', 'airports with increasingly massive security lines.', '机场的安全线越来越大。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6631, '2017考研英语一', 'But demanding too much of air travelers or providing too little security in return undermines public support for the process.', '但是要求太多的航空旅客或提供太少的安全保障会损害公众对该进程的支持。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6632, '2017考研英语一', 'Last year, the Transportation Security Administration (TSA) found in a secret check that undercover investigators were able to sneak weapons—both fake and real—past airport security nearly every time they tried.', '去年，交通安全管理局（TSA）在一次秘密检查中发现，卧底调查人员几乎每次尝试都能够偷窃武器，包括假的和真实的机场安全。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6633, '2017考研英语一', 'It is not yet clear how much more effective airline security has become—but the lines are obvious.', '目前还不清楚航空安全的有效性有多大，但线是显而易见的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6634, '2017考研英语一', 'Part of the issue is that the government did not anticipate the steep increase in airline travel, so the TSA is now rushing to get new screeners on the line.', '部分原因是政府没有预料到航空旅行的急剧增加，所以运输安全管理局现在正急着在网上推出新的筛选器。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6635, '2017考研英语一', 'There is one step the TSA could take that would not require remodeling airports or rushing to hire: Enroll more people in the PreCheck program.', 'TSA可以采取的一个步骤是不需要改建机场或匆忙雇佣：在预检查项目中招收更多的人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6636, '2017考研英语一', 'Passengers who pass a background check are eligible to use expedited screening lanes.', '通过背景检查的乘客有资格使用快速筛选车道。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6637, '2017考研英语一', 'This allows the TSA to focus on travellers who are higher risk, saving time for everyone involved.', '这允许TSA专注于风险较高的旅行者，为每个人节省时间。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6638, '2017考研英语一', 'The TSA wants to enroll 25 million people in PreCheck.', 'TSA希望在PreCheck招收2500万人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6639, '2017考研英语一', 'It has not gotten anywhere close to that, and one big reason is sticker shock.', '它没有达到任何接近，一个很大的原因是贴纸休克。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6640, '2017考研英语一', 'Passengers must pay $85 every five years to process their background checks.', '乘客必须每五年支付85美元来处理他们的背景调查。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6641, '2017考研英语一', 'Upcoming reforms might bring the price to a more reasonable level.', '即将进行的改革可能会把价格提高到一个更合理的水平。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6642, '2017考研英语一', 'But Congress should look into doing so directly, by helping to finance PreCheck enrollment or to cut costs in other ways.', '但国会应该直接通过帮助预支注册经费或以其他方式削减成本来研究这一点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6643, '2017考研英语一', 'The TSA cannot continue diverting resources into underused PreCheck lanes while most of the traveling public suffers in unnecessary lines.', '运输安全管理局不能继续将资源转移到使用不足的预检车道，而大多数旅客则处于不必要的线路中。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6644, '2017考研英语一', 'It is long past time to make the program work.', '要使程序工作已经过去很久了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6645, '2017考研英语一', 'Which of the following contributions to long waits at major airport.', '下列哪项贡献长期等待在主要机场？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6646, '2017考研英语一', 'The word \"expedited\" (Line 4, Para.', '“加速”一词（第4行，Para）。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6647, '2017考研英语一', 'Which of the following would be the best title for the text.', '下列哪一个将是最佳的文本标题？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6648, '2017考研英语一', 'Star watchers were among the most esteemed members of Hawaiian society.', '明星观察家是夏威夷社会最受尊敬的成员之一。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6649, '2017考研英语一', 'Sadly, all is not well with astronomy in Hawaii today.', '遗憾的是，今天夏威夷的天文学都不好。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6650, '2017考研英语一', 'Opposition to telescopes on Mauna Kea is nothing new.', '反对莫纳克亚山上的望远镜并不是什么新鲜事。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6651, '2017考研英语一', 'A small but vocal group of Hawaiians and environments have long viewed their presence as disrespect for sacred land and a painful reminder of the occupation of what was once a sovereign nation.', '一小群夏威夷人和环保人士长期以来一直认为他们的存在是对神圣土地的不尊重，是对曾经是一个主权国家的占领的痛苦提醒。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6652, '2017考研英语一', 'Some blame for the current controversy belongs to astronomers.', '对当前争论的一些指责属于天文学家。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6653, '2017考研英语一', 'In their eagerness to build bigger telescopes, they forgot that science is not the only way of understanding the world.', '在他们渴望建造更大的望远镜时，他们忘记了科学并不是理解世界的唯一途径。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6654, '2017考研英语一', 'Yet science has a cultural history, too, with roots going back to the dawn of civilization.', '然而科学也有文化的历史，其根源可以追溯到文明的曙光。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6655, '2017考研英语一', 'Calls to disassemble all telescopes on Mauna Kea or to ban future development there ignore the reality that astronomy and Hawaiian culture both seek to answer big questions about who we are, where we come from and where we are going.', '要求拆卸Mauna Kea上的所有望远镜或禁止在那里未来发展的呼声忽略了这样一个事实，即天文学和夏威夷文化都试图回答关于我们是谁、我们来自哪里、我们要去哪里的大问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6656, '2017考研英语一', 'Perhaps that is why we explore the starry skies, as if answering a primal calling to know ourselves and our true ancestral homes.', '也许这就是我们探索星空的原因，就好像回答一个原始的召唤来了解我们自己和我们真正的祖籍。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6657, '2017考研英语一', 'The astronomy community is making compromises to change its use of Mauna Kea.', '天文学界正在做出妥协改变莫纳克亚山的使用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6658, '2017考研英语一', 'To limit the number of telescopes on Mauna Kea, old ones will be removed at the end of their lifetimes and their sites returned to a natural state.', '为了限制Mauna Kea上的望远镜数量，旧望远镜将在其寿命结束时被拆除，并且它们的位置将恢复到自然状态。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6659, '2017考研英语一', 'There is no reason why everyone cannot be welcomed on Mauna Kea to embrace their cultural heritage and to study the stars.', '莫纳克亚山没有理由欢迎所有人接受他们的文化遗产和研究明星。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6660, '2017考研英语一', '\" With Britain voting to leave the European Union, and GDP already predicted to slow as a result, it is now a timely moment to assess what he was referring to.', '随着英国投票决定退出欧盟，而国内生产总值（GDP）预计将因此放缓，现在正是评估他所指的是什么的时刻。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6661, '2017考研英语一', 'The question of GDP and its usefulness has annoyed policymakers for over half a century.', 'GDP问题及其有用性已经困扰了政策制定者长达半个多世纪。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6662, '2017考研英语一', 'Many argue that it is a flawed concept.', '许多人认为这是一个有缺陷的概念。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6663, '2017考研英语一', 'It measures things that do not matter and misses things that do.', '它测量不重要的事情，忽略那些做的事情。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6664, '2017考研英语一', 'Across the 163 countries measured, the UK is one of the poorest performers in ensuring that economic growth is translated into meaningful improvements for its citizens.', '在衡量的163个国家中，英国是确保经济增长转化为对其公民有意义的改善方面表现最差的国家之一。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6665, '2017考研英语一', 'While all of these countries face their own challenges, there are a number of consistent themes.', '虽然所有这些国家都面临着自己的挑战，但也有许多一致的主题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6666, '2017考研英语一', 'Some relatively poor European countries have seen huge improvements across measures including civil society, income equality and the environment.', '一些相对贫穷的欧洲国家在包括公民社会、收入平等和环境在内的各项措施上都取得了巨大的进步。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6667, '2017考研英语一', 'So, what Kennedy was referring to was that while GDP has been the most common method for measuring the economic activity of nations, as a measure, it is no longer enough.', '因此，肯尼迪指的是，虽然GDP已经成为衡量各国经济活动最常用的方法，但作为衡量标准，它已不再足够。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6668, '2017考研英语一', 'Which of the following is true about the recent annual study.', '关于最近的年度研究，下列哪一项是正确的？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6669, '2017考研英语一', 'Which of the following is the best title for the text.', '以下哪一个是最佳的文本标题？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6670, '2017考研英语一', 'But it did so while holding its nose at the ethics of his conduct, which included accepting gifts such as a Rolex watch and a Ferrari automobile from a company seeking access to government.', '但这样做的同时，它嗤之以鼻的道德行为，其中包括接受礼品，如劳力士手表和法拉利汽车从一家公司寻求进入政府。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6671, '2017考研英语一', 'The court did suggest that accepting favors in return for opening doors is \"distasteful\" and \"nasty.', '法院确实建议接受作为开门的恩惠是“令人厌恶的”和“讨厌的”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6672, '2017考研英语一', 'Simply arranging a meeting, making a phone call, or hosting an event is not an \"official act\".', '简单地安排会议、打电话或举办一个活动并不是一种“官方行为”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6673, '2017考研英语一', 'Elected leaders must be allowed to help supporters deal with bureaucratic problems without fear of prosecution for bribery.', '当选的领导人必须被允许帮助支持者处理官僚问题，而不必担心贿赂会被起诉。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6674, '2017考研英语一', '\" The basic compact underlying representative government,\" wrote Chief Justice John Roberts for the court,\" assumes that public officials will hear from their constituents and act on their concerns.', '首席大法官约翰·罗伯茨（John Roberts）在法庭上写道：“代表政府的基本契约假定政府官员将听取选民的意见，并根据他们的关切采取行动。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6675, '2017考研英语一', '\" But the ruling reinforces the need for citizens and their elected representatives, not the courts, to ensure equality of access to government.', '但该裁决加强了公民及其民选代表，而不是法院，确保平等进入政府的必要性。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6676, '2017考研英语一', 'Favoritism in official access can fan public perceptions of corruption.', '官员准入中的偏袒会激起公众对腐败的看法。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6677, '2017考研英语一', 'But it is not always corruption.', '但这并不总是腐败。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6678, '2017考研英语一', 'Rather officials must avoid double standards, or different types of access for average people and the wealthy.', '更确切地说，官员必须避免双重标准，或者对普通人和富人的不同类型的准入。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6679, '2017考研英语一', 'If connections can be bought, a basic premise of democratic society—that all are equal in treatment by government—is undermined.', '如果可以买到联系，民主社会的一个基本前提——即所有国家在政府待遇上平等——就会受到破坏。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6680, '2017考研英语一', 'Good governance rests on an understanding of the inherent worth of each individual.', '好的治理在于理解每个人的内在价值。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6681, '2017考研英语一', 'The underlined sentence (Para.', '下划线的句子（Para）。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6682, '2017考研英语一', 'Paragraphs B and D have been correctly placed.', 'B段和D段已正确放置。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6683, '2017考研英语一', 'Mark your answers on ANSWER SHEET.', '马克在答题纸上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6684, '2017考研英语一', 'From then on his sketches, which appeared under the pen name \"Boz\" in The Evening Chronicle, earned him a modest reputation.', '从那时起，他就出现在晚报笔名“博兹”的草图上，为他赢得了一个不小的名声。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6685, '2017考研英语一', 'There were Pickwick coats and Pickwick cigars, and the plump, spectacled hero, Samuel Pickwick, became a national figure.', '有匹克威克外套和匹克威克雪茄，胖胖的、戴眼镜的英雄Samuel Pickwick成了一个全国性的人物。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6686, '2017考研英语一', 'After the first installment, Dickens wrote to the artist and asked him to correct a drawing Dickens felt was not faithful enough to his prose.', '在第一期之后，狄更斯写信给画家，要求他改正一幅狄更斯觉得对自己的散文不够忠实的画。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6687, '2017考研英语一', 'Seymour made the change, went into his backyard, and expressed his displeasure by committing suicide.', 'Seymour做出了改变，走进了他的后院，并表示自杀的不满。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6688, '2017考研英语一', 'Dickens and his publishers simply pressed on with a new artist.', '狄更斯和他的出版商只是和一位新的艺术家合作。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6689, '2017考研英语一', 'The comic novel, The Posthumous Papers of the Pickwick Club, appeared serially in 1836 and 1837, and was first published in book form in 1837.', '喜剧小说《匹克威克俱乐部的遗书》连载于1836年和1837年，并于1837年首次以书籍形式出版。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6690, '2017考研英语一', 'A moralist, satirist, and social reformer.', '道德家、讽刺作家和社会改革家。');
