INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6731, '2017考研英语二', 'Such visions are based on the 12 of being unemployed in a society built on the concept of employment.', '这种设想是建立在以就业为基础的社会中失业12的基础上的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6732, '2017考研英语二', 'In the 13 of work, a society designed with other ends in mind could 14 strikingly different circumstances for the future of labor and leisure.', '在13的工作中，一个设计了其他目的的社会可以为未来的劳动和休闲创造14个截然不同的环境。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6733, '2017考研英语二', 'Today, the 15 of work may be a bit overblown.', '今天，15的工作可能有些夸张。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6734, '2017考研英语二', '\"Many jobs are boring, degrading, unhealthy, and a waste of human potential,\" says John Danaher, a lecturer at the National University of Ireland in Galway.', '“许多工作都是无聊的、有辱人格的、不健康的，而且浪费了人的潜能，”爱尔兰国立大学高威分校的讲师约翰·达纳赫说。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6735, '2017考研英语二', 'These days, because leisure time is relatively 16 for most workers, people use their free time to counterbalance the intellectual and emotional 17 of their jobs.', '如今，因为对大多数工人来说，闲暇时间相对来说是16岁，人们利用他们的闲暇时间来平衡他们工作的智力和情感。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6736, '2017考研英语二', 'Answer the questions below each text by choosing A, B, C or D.', '通过选择A、B、C或D回答每个文本下面的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6737, '2017考研英语二', 'Mark your answers on the ANSWER SHEET.', '马克在答题纸上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6738, '2017考研英语二', 'Events are free, staffed by thousands of volunteers.', '活动是免费的，由数千名志愿者组成。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6739, '2017考研英语二', 'Parkrun is succeeding where London\'s Olympic \"legacy\" is failing.', 'PARKRUNE在伦敦奥运会“遗产”失败的情况下取得了成功。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6740, '2017考研英语二', 'Planning documents pledged that the great legacy of the Games would be to level a nation of sport lovers away from their couches.', '规划文件保证，奥运会的伟大遗产将是让体育爱好者们远离他们的沙发。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6741, '2017考研英语二', 'The population would be fitter, healthier and produce more winners.', '人口将更健康，更健康，并产生更多的赢家。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6742, '2017考研英语二', 'Worse, the numbers are now falling at an accelerating rate.', '更糟糕的是，这些数字现在正以加速的速度下降。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6743, '2017考研英语二', 'The opposition claims primary school pupils doing at least two hours of sport a week have nearly halved.', '反对党声称小学生每周至少做两个小时的运动几乎已经减半。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6744, '2017考研英语二', 'Obesity has risen among adults and children.', '肥胖在成人和儿童中有所上升。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6745, '2017考研英语二', '\" The success of Parkrun offers answers.', '“Parkrun的成功提供了答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6746, '2017考研英语二', 'Parkun is not a race but a time trial: Your only competitor is the clock.', 'PARKUN不是一场赛跑，而是一次计时赛：你唯一的对手是时钟。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6747, '2017考研英语二', 'The ethos welcomes anybody.', '民族欢迎任何人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6748, '2017考研英语二', 'The Olympic bidders, by contrast, wanted to get more people doing sports and to produce more elite athletes.', '相比之下，奥运会竞标者希望更多的人从事体育运动，并培养出更多的优秀运动员。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6749, '2017考研英语二', 'The dual aim was mixed up: The stress on success over taking part was intimidating for newcomers.', '双重目标被混淆了：成功的压力对新人来说是一种威胁。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6750, '2017考研英语二', 'Indeed, there is something a little absurd in the state getting involved in the planning of such a fundamentally \"grassroots\", concept as community sports associations.', '的确，这个国家参与到诸如社区体育协会这样的基本“基层”概念的规划中，有点荒唐。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6751, '2017考研英语二', 'But successive governments have presided over selling green spaces, squeezing money from local authorities and declining attention on sport in education.', '但是历届政府都主持着出售绿地、从地方政府那里榨取资金以及减少对教育中体育的关注。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6752, '2017考研英语二', 'Instead of wordy, worthy strategies, future governments need to do more to provide the conditions for sport to thrive.', '未来政府需要采取更多措施，为体育事业的繁荣提供条件，而不是冗长而有价值的策略。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6753, '2017考研英语二', 'Or at least not make them worse.', '或者至少不会让他们更糟。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6754, '2017考研英语二', '\"Tech is designed to really suck on you in,\" says Jenny Radesky in her study of digital play, \"and digital products are there to promote maximal engagement.', '珍妮·雷迪奇在研究数字游戏时说：“科技是设计来吸引你的，而数字产品是为了促进最大程度的参与。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6755, '2017考研英语二', 'During a separate observation, she saw that phones became a source of tension in the family.', '在另一次观察中，她发现手机成为家庭紧张的根源。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6756, '2017考研英语二', 'Parents would be looking at their emails while the children would be making excited bids for their attention.', '父母们会看着他们的电子邮件，而孩子们会为他们的注意力做出兴奋的出价。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6757, '2017考研英语二', 'Parents, he says, can get a lot out of using their devices to speak to a friend or get some work out of the way.', '他说，父母可以利用他们的设备与朋友交谈或得到一些工作。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6758, '2017考研英语二', 'This can make them feel happier, which lets then be more available to their child the rest of the time.', '这会让他们感到更快乐，让他们在余下的时间里更容易得到他们的孩子。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6759, '2017考研英语二', 'After all, if everyone you know is going to college in the fall, it seems silly to stay back a year, doesn\'t it.', '毕竟，如果你认识的每个人都将在秋季上大学，那么呆一年似乎是愚蠢的，不是吗？');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6760, '2017考研英语二', 'There\'s always a constant fear of falling behind everyone else on the socially perpetuated \"race to the finish line,\" whether that be toward graduate school, medical school or lucrative career.', '人们总是担心在社会上持续的“冲向终点”的竞赛中落后于其他人，不管是研究生院、医学院还是有利可图的职业。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6761, '2017考研英语二', 'Studies from the United States and Australia show that students who take a gap year are generally better prepared for and perform better in college than those who do not.', '来自美国和澳大利亚的研究表明，休学年的学生通常比那些没有休学年的学生准备得更好，在大学表现得更好。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6762, '2017考研英语二', 'Gap year experiences can lessen the blow when it comes to adjusting to college and being thrown into a brand new environment, making it easier to focus on academics and activities rather than acclimation blunders.', '当谈到适应大学环境，并被投入到一个全新的环境时，空档年的经历可以减轻这种打击，使得人们更容易关注学术和活动，而不是习惯性的失误。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6763, '2017考研英语二', 'If you\'re not convinced of the inherent value in taking a year off to explore interests, then consider its financial impact on future academic choices.', '如果你不相信休假一年来探索兴趣的固有价值，那么考虑一下它对未来学术选择的经济影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6764, '2017考研英语二', 'At Boston College, for example, you would have to complete an extra year were you to switch to the nursing school from another department.', '例如，在波士顿学院，如果你从另一个系转到护理学校，你就得多完成一年的学习。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6765, '2017考研英语二', 'Taking a gap year to figure things out initially can help prevent stress and save money later on.', '花一年的时间来解决问题，有助于预防压力，并在以后节省开支。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6766, '2017考研英语二', 'As Moritz puts it, how often are federal dollars building homes that are likely to be lost to a wildfire.', '正如莫里兹所说的那样，联邦政府建造房屋的频率很可能会被野火烧毁。');
