INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6816, '2017考研英语二', 'I love creating,\" he says.', '我喜欢创作，”他说。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6817, '2017考研英语二', 'To let the overseas students know much about our Chinese culture, I think that my presentation is supposed to include at least two key points.', '为了让海外学生更多地了解我们的中国文化，我认为我的演讲应该包括至少两个要点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6818, '2017考研英语二', 'On the one hand, I will put much stress on the history of China.', '一方面，我要强调中国的历史。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6819, '2017考研英语二', 'You must know that our China is an ancient country with a pretty long history.', '你必须知道我们的中国是一个有着悠久历史的古老国家。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6820, '2017考研英语二', 'On the other hand, my second strong point should be put on the main diet in China.', '另一方面，我的第二个优势应该放在中国的主要饮食上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6821, '2017考研英语二', 'Those two points are what I would like to emphasize, and I would like to know of your opinions on this and I wish you could give me some further ideas on it.', '这两点是我想强调的，我想知道你们对此的看法，我希望你们能给我一些进一步的意见。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6822, '2017考研英语二', 'I am looking forward to your reply.', '我期待着您的答复。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6823, '2017考研英语二', '1 million during this period.', '100万在此期间。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6824, '2017考研英语二', 'At least two fundamental factors could be identified to contribute to this phenomenon.', '至少有两个基本因素可以确定有助于这种现象。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6825, '2017考研英语二', 'In addition, there is no denying that the authorities concerned have issued a series of preferential policies to protect and promote the development of cultural industry, which encourages a widespread extension of visitors.', '此外，不可否认，有关部门出台了一系列优惠政策，保护和促进文化产业的发展，鼓励了游客的广泛传播。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6826, '2017考研英语二', 'From what has been discussed above, we may safely draw the conclusion that this trend will certainly maintain for quite a while in the near future, which will be of great benefits to our country and individual as well.', '通过以上讨论，我们可以安全地得出这样的结论，即这一趋势在不久的将来肯定会保持相当长的一段时间，这对我国和个人也将是非常有益的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6827, '2018考研英语一', 'On the other hand, putting your 2, in the wrong place often carries a high 3.', '另一方面，把你的2，在错误的地方往往携带高3。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6828, '2018考研英语一', '5 people place their trust in an individual or an institution, their brains release oxytocin, a hormone that 6 pleasurable feelings and triggers the herding instruct that prompts humans to 7 with one another.', '5人相信一个人或一个机构，他们的大脑释放催产素，一种6种愉悦感觉的荷尔蒙，并触发放牧指令，促使人类相互之间达到7。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6829, '2018考研英语一', '11 for us, we also have a sixth sense for dishonesty that may 12 us.', '11，对我们来说，在5月12日我们也有第六种不诚实的感觉。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6830, '2018考研英语一', 'A Canadian study found that children as young as 14 months can differentiate 13 a credible person and a dishonest one.', '加拿大的一项研究发现，14个月大的孩子可以区分13个可信的人和一个不诚实的人。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6831, '2018考研英语一', 'Sixty toddlers were each 14 to an adult tester holding a plastic container.', '六十个幼儿每14个成人测试一个塑料容器。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6832, '2018考研英语一', 'Among the children who had not been tricked, the majority were 18 to cooperate with the tester in learning a new skill, demonstrating that they trusted his leadership.', '在没有被欺骗的孩子中，大多数是18岁，他们和测试者合作学习新技能，这表明他们信任他的领导。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6833, '2018考研英语一', 'Answer the questions below each text by choosing A, B, C or D.', '通过选择A、B、C或D回答每个文本下面的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6834, '2018考研英语一', 'Mark your answers on the ANSWER SHEET.', '马克在答题纸上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6835, '2018考研英语一', 'jobs are at high risk of being automated, according to a University of Oxford study, with the middle class disproportionately squeezed.', '根据牛津大学的一项研究，随着中产阶级的压力越来越大，工作被自动化的风险越来越高。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6836, '2018考研英语一', 'The rich own the robots, so they will be fine.', '富人拥有机器人，所以他们会很好。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6837, '2018考研英语一', 'Optimists point out that technological upheaval has benefited workers in the past.', '乐观主义者指出，过去的技术动荡使工人受益匪浅。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6838, '2018考研英语一', 'Likewise, automation should eventually boost productivity, stimulate demand by driving down prices, and free workers from hard, boring work.', '同样，自动化最终应该提高生产率，通过压低价格刺激需求，使工人从辛苦、无聊的工作中解放出来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6839, '2018考研英语一', 'The first step, as Erik Brynjolfsson and Andrew McAfee argue in The Second Machine Age, should be rethinking education and job training.', '正如Erik Brynjolfsson和Andrew McAfee在《第二机器时代》中所说的，第一步应该是重新思考教育和职业培训。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6840, '2018考研英语一', 'Online education can supplement the traditional kind.', '网络教育可以补充传统的教育方式。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6841, '2018考研英语一', 'It could make extra training and instruction affordable.', '它可以使额外的训练和指导负担得起。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6842, '2018考研英语一', 'Professionals trying to acquire new skills will be able to do so without going into debt.', '试图获得新技能的专业人士能够在不负债的情况下做到这一点。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6843, '2018考研英语一', 'The challenge of coping with automation underlines the need for the U.', '应对自动化的挑战凸显了对美国的需求。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6844, '2018考研英语一', 'to revive its fading business dynamism: Starting new companies must be made easier.', '要恢复其日渐衰退的商业活力：启动新公司必须更容易。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6845, '2018考研英语一', 'In previous eras of drastic technological change, entrepreneurs smoothed the transition by dreaming up ways to combine labor and machines.', '在之前剧烈技术变革的时代，企业家们通过想出将劳动力和机器结合起来的方法平滑了这种转变。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6846, '2018考研英语一', 'needs the new companies that will invent them.', '需要新公司来发明它们。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6847, '2018考研英语一', 'Finally, because automation threatens to widen the gap between capital income and labor income, taxes and the safety net will have to be rethought.', '最后，由于自动化威胁着扩大资本收入和劳动收入之间的差距，税收和安全网将不得不重新考虑。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6848, '2018考研英语一', 'Technology will improve society in ways big and small over the next few years, yet this will be little comfort to those who find their lives and careers upended by automation.', '未来几年，科技将以大大小小的方式改善社会，但对于那些发现自己的生活和职业被自动化所颠覆的人来说，这将是一点安慰。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6849, '2018考研英语一', 'Destroying the machines that are coming for our jobs would be nuts.', '摧毁即将到来的工作机器将是一件棘手的事情。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6850, '2018考研英语一', 'But policies to help workers adapt will be indispensable.', '但是帮助工人适应的政策是必不可少的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6851, '2018考研英语一', 'Most Americans rely on social media to check daily headlines.', '大多数美国人依靠社交媒体来检查日常头条新闻。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6852, '2018考研英语一', 'Yet as distrust has risen toward all media, people may be starting to beef up their media literacy skills.', '然而，随着对所有媒体的不信任感上升，人们可能开始增强他们的媒介素养技能。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6853, '2018考研英语一', 'Such a trend is badly needed.', '这种趋势是迫切需要的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6854, '2018考研英语一', 'And a survey conducted for BuzzFeed News found 44 percent of Facebook users rarely or never trust news from the media giant.', '对BuffFo食新闻进行的调查发现，44%的脸谱网用户很少或从不信任媒体巨头的消息。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6855, '2018考研英语一', 'Young people who are digital natives are indeed becoming more skillful at separating fact from fiction in cyberspace.', '数字本地的年轻人在网络空间的虚构和虚构方面确实变得更加熟练。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6856, '2018考研英语一', '\"Many young people assume a great deal of personal responsibility for educating themselves and actively seeking out opposing viewpoints,\" the survey concluded.', '调查总结道：“许多年轻人承担着教育自己和积极寻找对立观点的许多个人责任。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6857, '2018考研英语一', 'Such active research can have another effect.', '这种积极的研究可以产生另一种效果。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6858, '2018考研英语一', 'This forces users to be more conscious of their role in passing along information.', '这迫使用户更加意识到他们在传递信息方面的作用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6859, '2018考研英语一', 'About a third say the problem of fake news lies in \"misinterpretation or exaggeration of actual news\" via social media.', '大约有第三的人说虚假新闻的问题在于通过社交媒体对“真实新闻的误解或夸大”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6860, '2018考研英语一', 'In other words, the choice to share news on social media may be the heart of the issue.', '换句话说，在社交媒体上分享新闻的选择可能是问题的核心。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6861, '2018考研英语一', '\"This indicates there is a real personal responsibility in counteracting this problem,\" says Roxanne Stone, editor in chief at Barna Group.', 'Barna Group的主编Roxanne Stone说：“这表明在解决这个问题时有真正的个人责任。”');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6862, '2018考研英语一', 'The potential of this work applied to healthcare is very great, but it could also lead to further concentration of power in the tech giants.', '这项工作应用于医疗保健的潜力很大，但也可能导致科技巨头进一步集中力量。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6863, '2018考研英语一', 'It Is against that background that the information commissioner, Elizabeth Denham, has issued her damning verdict against the Royal Free hospital trust under the NHS, which handed over to DeepMind the records of 1.', '正是在这种背景下，信息专员伊丽莎白·丹汉姆发表了针对英国国民健康保险制度下的皇家自由医院信托机构的谴责性裁决，该信托机构将1份记录交给了DeepMind。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6864, '2018考研英语一', 'DeepMind has almost apologized.', 'DeepMind几乎已经道歉了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6865, '2018考研英语一', 'The NHS trust has mended its ways.', 'NHS信托基金已经修复了它的方式。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6866, '2018考研英语一', 'There are lessons about informed patient consent to learn.', '有知情病人同意学习的教训。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6867, '2018考研英语一', 'But privacy is not the only angle in this case and not even the most important.', '但隐私并不是唯一的角度，甚至不是最重要的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6868, '2018考研英语一', 'Ms Denham chose to concentrate the blame on the NHS trust, since under existing law it \"controlled\" the data and DeepMind merely \"processed\" it.', '丹汉姆女士选择把责任集中在NHS的信托上，因为根据现有法律，它“控制”数据，而DeepMind只是“处理”数据。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6869, '2018考研英语一', 'But this distinction misses the point that it is processing and aggregation, not the mere possession of bits, that gives the data value.', '但是这种区别忽略了这一点，即给出数据值的是处理和聚合，而不是仅仅拥有位。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6870, '2018考研英语一', 'The great question is who should benefit from the analysis of all the data that our lives now generate.', '最大的问题是谁应该从我们现在生活中产生的所有数据的分析中受益。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6871, '2018考研英语一', 'Privacy law builds on the concept of damage to an individual from identifiable knowledge about them.', '隐私法是建立在个人对他们的可识别知识的损害概念之上的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6872, '2018考研英语一', 'That misses the way the surveillance economy works.', '这就忽略了监视经济的运作方式。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6873, '2018考研英语一', 'The data of an individual there gains its value only when it is compared with the data of countless millions more.', '一个人的数据只有在与数以百万计的数据进行比较时才有价值。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6874, '2018考研英语一', 'This practice does not address the real worry.', '这种做法并不能解决真正的忧虑。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6875, '2018考研英语一', 'It is not enough to say that the algorithms DeepMind develops will benefit patients and save lives.', '仅仅说心灵深处的算法将有益于病人和挽救生命是不够的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6876, '2018考研英语一', 'What matters is that they will belong to a private monopoly which developed them using public resources.', '重要的是，它们将属于私人垄断，利用公共资源开发私人垄断。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6877, '2018考研英语一', 'If software promises to save lives on the scale that dugs now can, big data may be expected to behave as a big pharm has done.', '如果软件承诺在目前的规模上挽救生命，那么大数据可能会像一个大型制药公司那样行动。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6878, '2018考研英语一', 'We are still at the beginning of this revolution and small choices now may turn out to have gigantic consequences later.', '我们仍处在这场革命的开端，现在的小选择可能会产生巨大的后果。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6879, '2018考研英语一', 'A long struggle will be needed to avoid a future of digital feudalism.', '为了避免数字封建主义的未来，需要长期的斗争。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6880, '2018考研英语一', 'It reported a net loss of $5.', '该公司净亏损5美元。');
