INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6932, '2018考研英语一', 'The ceremony will be held in the Sports Hall of our university on this Friday morning, from 9 a.', '颁奖仪式将于本星期五上午9点在我校体育馆举行。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6933, '2018考研英语一', 'The details about the ceremony are as follows.', '有关仪式的详情如下。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6934, '2018考研英语一', 'First and foremost, the president will make a speech for the graduates, blessing them to have a bright future.', '首先，校长将为毕业生们演讲，祝福他们有一个光明的未来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6935, '2018考研英语一', 'In addition, several experts will be invited to issuing certificates to all the graduates.', '此外，还会邀请几位专家向所有毕业生颁发证书。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6936, '2018考研英语一', 'It would be a great honor for us to have the accompany of all of you in the graduation ceremony.', '能在毕业典礼上为大家伴奏，我们将莫大的荣幸。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6937, '2018考研英语一', 'Therefore, we all hope that you can spare your time to attend it and we are looking forward to your reply to tell us whether you can attend it or not on that day.', '因此，我们都希望您能抽出时间来参加，我们期待着您的回复，告诉我们您当天是否能参加。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6938, '2018考研英语一', 'It is beyond doubt that the painter aims to tell us that everyone, especially college students, should have the spirit of creation and innovation.', '毋庸置疑，这位画家的目的是要告诉我们，每一个人，尤其是大学生，都应该有创造和创新的精神。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6939, '2018考研英语一', 'To put it another way, innovation is an essential and indispensable role for anyone who wants to succeed.', '换言之，创新对于任何想成功的人来说都是不可或缺的重要角色。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6940, '2018考研英语一', 'This can be directly attributed to the fact that one may be caught in dilemma, at least once in life.', '这可以直接归因于一个事实，一个人可能陷入困境，至少一生中一次。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6941, '2018考研英语一', 'Such a dilemma may coincidentally be most difficult period in his life.', '这样的两难处境可能是他一生中最困难的时期。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6942, '2018考研英语一', 'Then there are two choices before him: making a creative choice or an easier one.', '在他面前有两种选择：做出创造性的选择或更容易的选择。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6943, '2018考研英语一', 'If he chooses the former and tries to break through the barrier, difficult as it will be, success will be the result one day.', '如果他选择前者，并试图突破障碍，尽管困难重重，但成功终将有一天。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6944, '2018考研英语一', 'However, although it seems to be much easier for him at the moment, the latter choice may kill off his dream and ambition, and such choice then will be a pity all his life.', '然而，虽然现在对他来说似乎要容易得多，但是后一种选择可能会扼杀他的梦想和抱负，而这样的选择将会是他一生的遗憾。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6945, '2018考研英语一', 'As college student, definitely, we are facing or will face many difficulties.', '作为大学生，当然，我们面临或将面临许多困难。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6946, '2018考研英语一', 'At such moment, we should bear in mind that creation is a necessary and indispensable quality in our life, a positive attitude to life and an approach to success.', '此时此刻，我们应该牢记，创造是我们生活中必不可少的一种品质，一种积极的生活态度，一种走向成功的方法。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6947, '2018考研英语一', 'Keep the spirit of innovation, and we will win a better life.', '保持创新精神，我们将赢得更好的生活。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6948, '2018考研英语二', 'The new research reveals that the need to know is so strong that people will 2 to satisfy their curiosity even when it is clear the answer will 3.', '新的研究表明，需要知道的是如此强烈，人们会2满足他们的好奇心，即使是很清楚答案是3。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6949, '2018考研英语二', 'In a series of four experiments, behavioral scientists at the University of Chicago and the Wisconsin School of Business tested.', '在一系列的四次实验中，芝加哥大学和威斯康星商学院的行为科学家进行了测试。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6950, '2018考研英语二', 'For one 5 each participant was shown a pile of pens that the researcher claimed were from a previous experiment.', '每5个参与者都会看到一堆钢笔，研究人员声称这是以前的实验。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6951, '2018考研英语二', 'Answer the questions below each text by choosing A, B, C or D.', '通过选择A、B、C或D回答每个文本下面的问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6952, '2018考研英语二', 'Mark your answers on the ANSWER SHEET.', '马克在答题纸上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6953, '2018考研英语二', 'Koziatek is part of something pioneering.', '科扎蒂克是创业的一部分。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6954, '2018考研英语二', 'He is a teacher at a New Hampshire high school where learning is not something of books and tests and mechanical memorization, but practical.', '他是新罕布什尔州一所高中的老师，在那里，学习不是书本、考试和机械记忆，而是实用的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6955, '2018考研英语二', 'Nothing is necessarily gained by forcing students to learn geometry at a graffitied desk stuck with generations of discarded chewing gum.', '强迫学生在被几代人丢弃的口香糖粘住的涂鸦桌子上学习几何学并不能得到任何东西。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6956, '2018考研英语二', 'They can also learn geometry by assembling a bicycle.', '他们还可以通过组装自行车来学习几何学。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6957, '2018考研英语二', 'Working with your hands is seen as almost a mark of inferiority.', '用手工作几乎是自卑的标志。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6958, '2018考研英语二', 'Schools in the family of vocational education \"have that stereotype.', '学校在职业教育家庭中有这种刻板印象。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6959, '2018考研英语二', 'Manufacturing is not the economic engine that it once was.', '制造业不是它曾经的经济引擎。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6960, '2018考研英语二', 'The job security that the US economy once offered to high school graduates has largely evaporated.', '美国经济曾经给高中毕业生提供的工作保障已经大大地蒸发了。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6961, '2018考研英语二', 'More education is the new principle.', '更多的教育是新的原则。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6962, '2018考研英语二', 'We want more for our kids, and rightfully so.', '我们想要更多的给我们的孩子，这是理所当然的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6963, '2018考研英语二', 'But only 44 percent of workers are adequately trained.', '但只有44%的工人得到了充分的培训。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6964, '2018考研英语二', 'In other words, at a time when the working class has turned the country on its political head, frustrated that the opportunity that once defined America is vanishing, one obvious solution is staring us in the face.', '换言之，在工人阶级已经改变了国家的政治头脑的时候，沮丧的是，一旦定义了美国的机会正在消失，一个显而易见的解决方案就是盯着我们。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6965, '2018考研英语二', 'There exists the prejudice that vocational education is for kids who.', '职业教育对孩子的偏见是存在的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6966, '2018考研英语二', 'We can infer from Paragraph 5 that high school graduates.', '我们可以从第5段推断高中毕业生。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6967, '2018考研英语二', 'The move to renewables is picking up momentum around the world: They now account for more than half of new power sources going on line.', '全球范围内转向可再生能源的势头正在加快：现在可再生能源占了新能源上网的一半以上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6968, '2018考研英语二', 'Some growth stems from a commitment by governments and farsighted businesses to fund cleaner energy sources.', '一些增长源于政府和有远见的企业为清洁能源提供资金的承诺。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6969, '2018考研英语二', 'But increasingly the story is about the plummeting prices of renewables, especially wind and solar.', '但越来越多的故事是关于可再生能源价格暴跌，特别是风能和太阳能。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6970, '2018考研英语二', 'In many parts of the world renewable energy is already a principal energy source.', '在世界许多地区，可再生能源已经成为主要能源。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6971, '2018考研英语二', 'In Scotland, for example, wind turbines provide enough electricity to power 95 percent of homes.', '例如，在苏格兰，风力涡轮机提供足够的电力为95%的家庭供电。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6972, '2018考研英语二', 'While the rest of the world takes the lead, notably China and Europe, the United States is also seeing a remarkable shift.', '虽然世界其他地区占主导地位，特别是中国和欧洲，美国也看到了一个显著的转变。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6973, '2018考研英语二', 'In a recent speech in Iowa, he dismissed wind power as an unreliable energy source.', '在爱荷华最近的一次演讲中，他把风力发电视为一种不可靠的能源。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6974, '2018考研英语二', 'But a boost in the storage capacity of batteries is making their ability to keep power flowing around the clock more likely.', '但是电池的存储容量的提高使他们保持电力昼夜不停流动的能力更为可能。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6975, '2018考研英语二', 'Although electric cars are still a rarity on roads now, this massive investment could change the picture rapidly in coming years.', '虽然电动汽车在道路上仍然是稀有的，但这种巨大的投资可能会在未来几年迅速改变局面。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6976, '2018考研英语二', 'The pace of change in energy sources appears to be speeding up—perhaps just in time to have a meaningful effect in slowing climate change.', '能源变化的步伐似乎在加快，或许正好对减缓气候变化产生有意义的影响。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6977, '2018考研英语二', 'According to Paragraph 3, the use of renewable energy in America.', '根据第3段，在美国使用可再生能源。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6978, '2018考研英语二', 'It can be learned that in Iowa,.', '可以得知，在爱荷华。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6979, '2018考研英语二', 'Even without knowing what was in the messages, the knowledge of who sent them and to whom was enormously revealing and still could be.', '即使不知道信息里有什么，关于是谁发送的，以及向谁发送的知识也是非常具有启示性的，而且仍然可以。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6980, '2018考研英语二', 'Competition law appears to be the only way to address these imbalances of power.', '竞争法似乎是解决这些权力失衡的唯一途径。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6981, '2018考研英语二', 'For one thing, it is very slow compared to the pace of Change within the digital economy.', '一方面，与数字经济的变化速度相比，这是非常缓慢的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6982, '2018考研英语二', 'By the time a problem has been addressed and remedied it may have vanished in the marketplace, to be replaced by new abuses of power.', '当一个问题得到解决和补救时，它可能已经消失在市场上，被新的滥用权力所取代。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6983, '2018考研英语二', 'But there is a deeper conceptual problem, too.', '但也存在更深层次的概念问题。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6984, '2018考研英语二', 'The users of their Services are not their customers.', '他们的服务使用者不是他们的顾客。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6985, '2018考研英语二', 'Just as some ants farm the bugs called aphids for the honeydew the produce when they feed, so Google farms us for the data that our digital lives yield.', '正如一些蚂蚁在喂食时为了生产蜜露而种植被称为蚜虫的昆虫一样，Google也在为我们提供数字生活产生的数据。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6986, '2018考研英语二', 'According to Paragraph 1, Facebook acquired WhatsApp for its.', '根据第1段，脸谱网收购了WhatsApp。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6987, '2018考研英语二', 'Linking phone numbers to Facebook identities may.', '将电话号码与脸谱网身份联系起来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6988, '2018考研英语二', 'According to the author, competition law.', '根据作者，竞争法。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6989, '2018考研英语二', 'Competition law as presently interpreted can hardly protect Facebook users because.', '目前的竞争法很难保护脸谱网用户。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6990, '2018考研英语二', 'The ants analogy is used to illustrate.', '蚂蚁类比是用来说明的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6991, '2018考研英语二', 'Whichever approach, the key is to determine your length of focus time and stick to it.', '无论哪种方法，关键是确定你的焦点时间长度并坚持它。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6992, '2018考研英语二', 'Newport also recommends \"deep scheduling\" to combat constant interruptions and get more done in less time.', '纽波特还建议“深度调度”以应对不断的中断，并在更短的时间内完成更多的工作。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6993, '2018考研英语二', '\"At any given point, I should have deep work scheduled for roughly the next mouth.', '“在任何给定的时间点，我都应该有一个大致的工作计划，大概在下一个嘴里。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6994, '2018考研英语二', 'In order to make the most of our focus and energy, we also need to embrace downtime, or as Newport suggests, \"be lazy\".', '为了充分利用我们的注意力和精力，我们也需要拥抱停工时间，或者像纽波特建议的那样，“懒惰”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6995, '2018考研英语二', 'When our brains switch between being focused and unfocused on a task, they tend to be more efficient.', '当我们的大脑在专注和不专注于一个任务之间切换时，他们往往会更有效率。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6996, '2018考研英语二', 'The key to mastering the art of deep work is to.', '掌握深层次艺术的关键是：');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6997, '2018考研英语二', 'According to Newport, idleness is.', '根据新港的说法，懒惰是。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6998, '2018考研英语二', 'This text is mainly about.', '本文主要是关于。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (6999, '2018考研英语二', 'There are two extra subtitles which you do not need to use.', '有两个额外的字幕，你不需要使用。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7000, '2018考研英语二', 'Mark your answers on the ANSWER SHEET.', '马克在答题纸上的答案。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7001, '2018考研英语二', 'Pay a unique compliment 4.', '给予独特的赞美4。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7002, '2018考研英语二', 'Name, places, things 5.', '姓名、地点、物品5。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7003, '2018考研英语二', 'Find the \"me too\"s 6.', '找到“我也是”的6。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7004, '2018考研英语二', 'Skip the small talk 7.', '跳过闲聊7。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7005, '2018考研英语二', 'Ask for an opinion Five ways to make conversation with anyone Conversations are links, which means when you have a conversation with a new person a link gets formed and every conversation you have after that moment will strengthen the link.', '征求意见五种与任何人对话的方式对话都是链接，这意味着当你与一个新人谈话时，一个链接就形成了，在那一刻之后你所有的对话都会加强这个链接。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7006, '2018考研英语二', 'You meet new people every day: the grocery worker, the cab driver, new people at work or the security guard at the door.', '你每天都会遇到新的人：杂货店工人、出租车司机、上班的新员工或者门口的保安。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7007, '2018考研英语二', 'Simply starting a conversation with them will form a link.', '简单地和他们开始交谈会形成联系。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7008, '2018考研英语二', 'Here are five simple ways that you can make the first move and start a conversation with strangers.', '这里有五种简单的方法，你可以第一次移动，开始与陌生人交谈。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7009, '2018考研英语二', 'I know the feeling and here is my advice: just get it out.', '我知道这种感觉，这是我的建议：把它弄出来。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7010, '2018考研英语二', 'So when someone tries to communicate with you, just be in that communication wh oleheartedly.', '因此，当有人试图与你交流时，就要全心全意地进行交流。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7011, '2018考研英语二', 'Trust me, eye contact is where all the magic hap pens.', '相信我，眼神接触是所有魔法笔的所在。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7012, '2018考研英语二', 'When you make eye contact, you can feel the conversation.', '当你眼神交流时，你能感觉到对话。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7013, '2018考研英语二', 'When you remember such things you can automatically become investor in their well being.', '当你记住这些事情时，你可以自动成为他们幸福的投资者。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7014, '2018考研英语二', 'Five amazing ways that you can make conversation with almost anyone.', '五种令人惊奇的方式，你几乎可以与任何人交谈。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7015, '2018考研英语二', 'Directions: Translate the following text into Chinese.', '说明：将下列文字翻译成中文。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7016, '2018考研英语二', 'Write your translation neatly on the ANSWER SHEET.', '把你的译文整齐地写在答题纸上。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7017, '2018考研英语二', 'He ticks \"astronaut\" , but quickly adds \"scientist\" to the list and selects it as well.', '他勾选了“宇航员”，但很快又把“科学家”添加到列表中，并选择了它。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7018, '2018考研英语二', 'The boy is convinced that if he reads enough, he can explore as many career paths as he likes.', '男孩相信如果他读够了，他可以探索他喜欢的职业道路。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7019, '2018考研英语二', 'He reads so passionately that his parents have to institute a \"no reading policy\" at the dinner table.', '他读得如此热情以至于他的父母不得不在餐桌上制定一个“禁止阅读的政策”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7020, '2018考研英语二', 'Gates chooses nonfiction titles because they explain how the world works.', '盖茨选择非小说类的标题，因为它们解释了世界是如何运作的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7021, '2018考研英语二', '\"Each book opens up new avenues of knowledge,\" Gates says.', '“每本书都开辟了新的知识途径，”Gates说。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7022, '2018考研英语二', 'In a final experiment, participants who were encouraged to 16 how they would feel after viewing an unpleasant picture were less likely to 17 to see such an image.', '在最后一个实验中，受试者被鼓励在观看不愉快的图片后16的感觉是不太可能看到17这样的图像。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7023, '2018考研英语二', 'imagining can help determine 19 it is worth the endeavor.', '想象可以帮助决定19，这是值得的努力。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7024, '2018考研英语二', 'So keep it simple: \"Hi\", \"Hey\" or \"Hello\"——do the best you can to gather all of the enthusiasm and energy you can, put on a big smile and say \"Hi\".', '所以，保持简单：“嗨”，“嗨”或“你好”——尽你所能聚集所有的热情和能量，微笑着说“嗨”。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7025, '2018考研英语二', 'Section IV Writing 51.', '第四节写作51。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7026, '2018考研英语二', 'Two days ago, I suddenly accepted the notice that there would be an academic meeting this Friday night in our department and everyone was asked to attend.', '两天前，我突然接受了通知，这个星期五晚上我们系要开学术会议，每个人都被邀请参加。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7027, '2018考研英语二', 'I know that my changing plan has definitely caused some inconvenience to you.', '我知道我的改变计划确实给你带来了一些不便。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7028, '2018考研英语二', 'I am so sorry for my failing to keep the promise of visiting you.', '我很抱歉未能遵守你的诺言。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7029, '2018考研英语二', 'Therefore, in order to make up this situation, I wonder if you could give me another chance and spare some time to meet me next Monday.', '因此，为了弥补这个局面，我想知道你能否再给我一次机会，下星期一抽出时间来见我。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7030, '2018考研英语二', 'I am so sorry for any inconvenience caused by me.', '我很抱歉给您带来的不便。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7031, '2018考研英语二', 'Hope you can accept my apology and arrange a new time for me to visit you.', '希望你能接受我的道歉，并安排一个新的时间让我来拜访你。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7032, '2018考研英语二', 'I am looking forward to your reply.', '我期待着您的答复。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7033, '2018考研英语二', 'Yours sincerely, Li Ming 52.', '你真诚的，李明52。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7034, '2018考研英语二', 'Among them, the proportion of service, environment, price and other factors is 26.', '其中，服务、环境、价格等因素的比例为26。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7035, '2018考研英语二', 'By contrast, the factor of focusing on features of the restaurant is in the lead, accounting for 36.', '相比之下，关注餐厅特色的因素占主导地位，占36。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7036, '2018考研英语二', 'Therefore, such a great proportion of citizens are more likely to focus on the features of a restaurant, instead of only concentrating on the price.', '因此，如此大比例的市民更倾向于关注餐厅的特色，而不是仅仅关注价格。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7037, '2018考研英语二', 'Moreover, in a society where living standard is highly advocated, citizens in mounting numbers in China, shrugging off their former habit of focusing on lower price, gradually find the service and environment of a restaurant is an essential factor.', '此外，在崇尚生活水平的社会中，越来越多的中国公民摆脱了以往注重低价的习惯，逐渐发现餐厅的服务和环境是一个重要因素。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7038, '2018考研英语二', 'According to a survey conducted by China Research Center, up to 87% Chinese people prefer to choose a comfortable and fashionable restaurant when they go out for eating.', '据中国研究中心进行的一项调查显示，多达87%的中国人在外出就餐时更喜欢选择舒适、时尚的餐厅。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7039, '2018考研英语二', 'Taking into account what has been argued so far, I am inclined to think about the current situation is normal.', '考虑到目前为止的争论，我倾向于认为当前的形势是正常的。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7040, '2018考研英语二', 'In view of the analysis above, it can be predicted that the trend will continue in the future.', '鉴于以上分析，可以预测这种趋势将在未来继续下去。');
INSERT INTO `sentence` VALUES (7041, '2018考研英语二', 'Accordingly, it is of no necessity for the public to regard it with too much consideration.', '因此，公众没有必要太多地考虑它。');
